WEBVTT

02:46.620 --> 02:48.578
<i>When I was still just a kid,</i>

02:49.040 --> 02:51.328
<i>I remember my father telling me</i>

02:51.709 --> 02:53.369
<i>what he thought that it took
for a man to be happy.</i>

02:55.087 --> 02:58.124
Tommy, finally! Come on, man,
New Year's is tonight.

02:58.299 --> 03:00.921
- I'm sorry I'm late.
- Don't worry. I covered for you.

03:01.052 --> 03:01.821
Thanks, Hank.

03:01.998 --> 03:03.836
What, did you stay out
till they hung the last dog?

03:03.837 --> 03:05.072
- Yeah.
- Ha!

03:05.307 --> 03:07.016
<i>Simple things, really...</i>

03:08.519 --> 03:09.801
<i>A wife he loves,</i>

03:11.147 --> 03:12.892
<i>a decent job,</i>

03:14.902 --> 03:17.061
<i>friends and neighbors
who like and respect him.</i>

03:18.030 --> 03:19.739
<i>And for a while there,</i>

03:20.784 --> 03:23.026
<i>without hardly even realizing it,</i>

03:23.829 --> 03:25.536
<i>I had all that.</i>

03:27.041 --> 03:28.784
<i>I was a happy man.</i>

03:29.877 --> 03:31.040
Hey, tom.

03:31.712 --> 03:33.421
Remember we talked about
me getting off early today?

03:42.602 --> 03:43.645
Hey, Hank!

03:44.727 --> 03:45.890
Hey, Happy New Year, Schmitt!

03:49.732 --> 03:51.275
- Hey, Linda, Happy New Year.
- Happy New Year.

03:51.443 --> 03:53.151
- Hey, where you guys going?
- Sledding!

03:53.362 --> 03:55.355
- Hey, can I come?
- No!

03:55.633 --> 03:57.184
Ohh... Please! Ohh!

04:06.251 --> 04:08.707
- Hey, Carl.
- Hey, happy new year, Hank.

04:08.879 --> 04:11.086
You gotta start charging people for that.

04:11.000 --> 04:14.333
Ha ha ha! Yeah, it'd pay better
than the county does.

04:32.197 --> 04:33.656
Honey, it's me.

04:38.288 --> 04:41.031
- How you feelin' today?
- Hey. Good.

04:43.670 --> 04:46.995
- Oh, my gosh.
- He was sure kickin' a lot today.

04:57.932 --> 04:59.293
Uh-oh...

05:00.896 --> 05:04.063
Looks like it's gonna be
a long afternoon for you.

05:04.233 --> 05:05.858
He brought Lou along.

05:06.569 --> 05:07.351
Oh, great.

05:07.529 --> 05:10.549
Yeah. I'll just be lyin' here, relaxing.

05:10.550 --> 05:12.566
- Oh...
- Ha ha ha!

05:16.247 --> 05:17.278
Hey, Jacob!

05:25.092 --> 05:26.439
Ha ha ha!

05:29.588 --> 05:31.147
What's he doing here?

05:31.322 --> 05:33.348
He needed a ride home.

05:33.442 --> 05:34.555
Little out of the way, isn't it?

05:35.386 --> 05:38.355
We can drop him off when we're done,
you know. It's no big deal, Hank.

05:40.425 --> 05:42.000
What's the big deal, Hank?

05:42.169 --> 05:46.084
Hey, you know, you need to shovel this shit
off of your, uh... whatcha-call-it deal there.

05:46.257 --> 05:48.165
I'll pay you a quarter to do it.

05:48.218 --> 05:50.249
Huh! I could use it.

05:50.703 --> 05:52.585
Ha ha! Look at Lou.

05:59.105 --> 06:00.433
Here, hold this, will you?

06:00.606 --> 06:03.100
- Wanna put it back there?
- No, no, it's gonna wilt.

06:03.067 --> 06:05.692
Hank, say hi to...
You didn't say hi to Mary Beth.

06:04.860 --> 06:06.605
Oh, yeah.
Hi, Mary Beth!

06:06.947 --> 06:09.520
He said hi, Mary Beth.

06:08.360 --> 06:09.716
Hank said hi.
Hi, Lou.

06:09.924 --> 06:10.967
Come here.

06:48.285 --> 06:49.613
Somebody else was here.

06:50.538 --> 06:52.079
Oh, I brought those.

06:53.582 --> 06:54.614
When?

06:55.273 --> 06:57.671
Well... What the hell do you think, Hank?

06:57.672 --> 07:00.545
This is the only day we can come here?

07:01.049 --> 07:02.876
What the hell's wrong with you?

07:04.136 --> 07:07.969
Hey, Jacob! Look!
I'm writing my name!

07:08.141 --> 07:11.640
Hang on a second!
Let me get Mrs. Johnson out here!

07:11.811 --> 07:13.270
I'll help you out.

07:36.323 --> 07:38.150
You know what the guy says?

07:38.325 --> 07:41.580
Says it's the crock pot
or, uh, crock box?

07:41.670 --> 07:48.082
No, no. Pay attention now...
Oh, no, that's the preacher, see?

07:45.792 --> 07:48.330
- This is the cowboy.
- Yeah, he says "moo."

07:48.962 --> 07:52.421
No, no. It's the guy standing
by the road. He says:

07:52.516 --> 07:55.449
"Why, officer? It's just a pine apple."

07:55.450 --> 07:57.006
- Ha ha ha!
- Ha ha!

07:57.313 --> 07:58.712
- You get it?
- Yeah.

07:59.682 --> 08:02.139
Well, Mr. accountant doesn't get it.

08:01.914 --> 08:03.061
Ha ha ha ha...

08:03.895 --> 08:04.937
Look out!

08:05.875 --> 08:06.918
Shit!

08:09.211 --> 08:10.462
You ok, baby?

08:11.153 --> 08:12.185
Go on, get out!

08:13.364 --> 08:15.073
Look at that, man!

08:15.909 --> 08:17.107
My truck.

08:18.788 --> 08:19.950
Come on, get out.

08:20.914 --> 08:21.614
Mary Beth!

08:25.754 --> 08:28.244
- She's gonna come back.
- Hey, what are you doing?

08:28.423 --> 08:30.665
- It's a nature preserve, you know that.
- So what?

08:30.842 --> 08:33.714
So you can't hunt here.
Come on, put the gun back.

08:33.971 --> 08:35.465
But it... but it messed up my truck.

08:35.640 --> 08:38.400
- So what? Come on.
- Hey, hey, Hank...

08:38.684 --> 08:42.843
It's not like we're huntin' here, uh-uh.

08:42.940 --> 08:44.648
- We're collectin' the dead.
- That's right.

08:45.067 --> 08:47.024
We're collecting the dead.

09:06.050 --> 09:08.544
- Just look at him...
- He runs like my wife.

09:08.718 --> 09:12.204
Hey, come on, wait up!
Come on, I'm not dressed for this shit!

09:27.399 --> 09:28.546
Mary Beth!

09:30.869 --> 09:32.529
Jesus! Look at all them birds!

09:32.787 --> 09:36.655
Those things are always waitin' on
something to die so they can eat it, right?

09:37.293 --> 09:39.499
What a weird job.

09:57.231 --> 09:59.106
Wish we had something to drink.

10:01.195 --> 10:02.986
Always be prepared.

10:03.155 --> 10:05.942
Oh, that's a good idea.
Let's all start drinking now.

10:06.117 --> 10:08.074
See there?
See how he is?

10:11.348 --> 10:13.906
Wonk! Dit-dit...
Like that guy, huh?

10:14.243 --> 10:16.006
Remember? Wonk! Dit-dit.
- Uh-huh.

10:16.545 --> 10:18.372
- You want some?
- I'm not thirsty.

10:18.548 --> 10:20.670
What, you don't drink till after 5:00?

10:20.775 --> 10:22.130
After 5:00, heh heh.

10:22.594 --> 10:24.407
Or maybe you just don't wanna share.

10:24.450 --> 10:26.710
You're afraid you'll catch
something from us, huh?

10:26.820 --> 10:27.872
Yeah...

10:28.000 --> 10:29.493
Hey, Hank!

10:29.502 --> 10:32.724
Hey! Come on, what are you doing?
Quit jackin' around.

10:33.147 --> 10:34.613
Now, you see...

10:34.614 --> 10:38.005
That's what you might call
an "insinuating" throw.

10:38.361 --> 10:39.357
Remember?

10:40.280 --> 10:43.566
You said that to me last time I saw you.

10:44.159 --> 10:47.493
Could've just said "hint".
But no, you had to put on airs.

10:48.122 --> 10:50.329
Show us all them fancy words you know.

10:50.470 --> 10:53.328
What, do you sit around,
you think about this stuff?

10:53.370 --> 10:55.239
When was that, two months ago?

10:56.590 --> 10:58.215
Kiss my ass.

11:00.553 --> 11:01.502
What the hell is it?

11:12.652 --> 11:15.731
- Jesus Christ.
- Shit, that's a airplane.

11:18.448 --> 11:22.779
You know what, it's probably
one of those drunk doctors.

11:20.510 --> 11:22.386
They're always crashing
their plane, you know?

11:23.922 --> 11:27.113
Yeah, it must've come down right there.
See all them broken trees, Jake?

11:27.292 --> 11:28.620
It's too dark. I can't see.

11:29.377 --> 11:31.833
Scrape some of that snow
off the windshield!

11:33.215 --> 11:35.753
Can't see a damn thing.

11:37.845 --> 11:39.043
Door's stuck.

11:39.221 --> 11:41.096
Probably a singer or something.

11:53.028 --> 11:54.773
Still can't see nothin' here.

11:57.223 --> 11:59.982
Still can't see anything.
Can't see a damn thing.

12:00.036 --> 12:01.579
I see the pilot!

12:03.774 --> 12:05.233
What's he talking about?

12:06.460 --> 12:07.540
Said somebody's in there.

12:10.089 --> 12:11.372
Are you ok?

12:14.303 --> 12:15.554
Hey. Hey, buddy...

12:16.388 --> 12:17.535
Aah! Whoaaa...

12:19.724 --> 12:20.871
Ah! Aah! Aah!

12:20.975 --> 12:22.226
Hey, get... get off!

12:23.164 --> 12:24.728
What the hell is going on...?

12:25.562 --> 12:26.709
Aah! Ohh!

12:27.647 --> 12:28.688
Oh, God!

12:28.689 --> 12:29.732
Shit!

12:30.946 --> 12:32.524
Hey, lemme outta here.

12:37.545 --> 12:40.698
- Good grief, Hank.
- Let me get this off of him. Here...

12:46.131 --> 12:48.923
Hank, did you... did you...
Did you see all them birds?

12:51.302 --> 12:53.130
Did I "see the birds"?!

12:54.056 --> 12:55.800
Come on, help me get outta here.

13:02.274 --> 13:04.816
- Hank, put that on your eye.
- Thanks.

13:05.026 --> 13:07.518
- You tore your coat, you know.
- Oh, my God!

13:08.030 --> 13:09.608
Oh, my God! Look at this!

13:10.953 --> 13:12.289
Shit!

13:12.590 --> 13:14.244
Oh, my God!

13:14.245 --> 13:15.409
How much you think is in here?

13:15.622 --> 13:19.371
God almighty! These are $100 bills!
The whole bag's full of 'em!

13:20.669 --> 13:22.413
Is this... is it real money, Lou?

13:22.589 --> 13:25.423
Oh, hell, yes, it's real.
Don't be stupid.

13:25.676 --> 13:28.002
Why would somebody be flying
around with this kind of cash?

13:28.178 --> 13:30.586
You know what? I bet
it's drug money.

13:29.675 --> 13:31.552
That's probably
I bet you're what it is. Right.

13:31.553 --> 13:33.216
This guy's a dope dealer

13:32.386 --> 13:33.220
because that's what they do.

13:33.392 --> 13:35.931
They fly around in
these little planes.

13:36.104 --> 13:38.310
- I guaran-damn-tee you, this is dirty money.
- That's right. I saw it on 20/20.

13:39.065 --> 13:41.734
"Dirty money"? What do you mean?
Are you telling me it's counterfeit?

13:41.735 --> 13:45.000
Oh, no.
No, this is real.

13:45.155 --> 13:48.192
Whatever it is, it's a police matter now.
What do you think we should do?

13:48.367 --> 13:50.241
Somebody should stay here,
somebody should go after the cops?

13:49.901 --> 13:52.701
- How you wanna Work it?
- What? Let's think this through.

13:52.850 --> 13:55.383
- What?
- Hold on!

13:56.544 --> 13:57.788
What if we didn't turn it in?

14:02.550 --> 14:03.926
You wanna keep it?

14:04.850 --> 14:08.000
Ha ha ha! He wants to keep it...
Well, that's a hot one!

14:08.120 --> 14:09.329
Why wouldn't we?

14:09.400 --> 14:10.713
- Why wouldn't we?
- Yeah.

14:10.834 --> 14:12.358
- Because we'd go to prison!
- Why?

14:12.686 --> 14:14.015
Why? Because it's stealing.

14:14.313 --> 14:15.973
"Stealing"...
Stealing from who?

14:16.148 --> 14:18.880
From him? Hell, he won't mind!

14:18.881 --> 14:19.871
Ha ha ha...

14:20.571 --> 14:22.309
Oh, 'cause he's dead, right?

14:23.385 --> 14:25.698
Ha ha! That's pretty funny...
He's dead, he won't mind.

14:26.368 --> 14:29.951
I say we take this bag back to the truck,
and we pretend like we were never here.

14:30.122 --> 14:31.036
Fuck yeah. Why not?

14:31.207 --> 14:33.034
Why not? Because we'd get caught.

14:33.376 --> 14:36.461
Aw, hell! I'll tell you what.
Stay the hell out of it then.

14:36.630 --> 14:40.544
You know, we don't need you.
It'd just be more money for us.

14:40.750 --> 14:43.252
Hey, I don't wanna stump you
another fancy word, Lou,

14:43.300 --> 14:45.297
but does the term "accomplice"
mean anything to you?

14:45.373 --> 14:46.467
Come on, that's stupid!

14:46.766 --> 14:49.258
But, Hank...
Why would we get caught?

14:49.436 --> 14:52.436
Because it's a lot of money, Jacob.
Somebody's bound to be looking for it.

14:52.500 --> 14:54.988
When they find that plane
and the money's not in it...

14:54.066 --> 14:55.624
- Bullshit!
- No, it's not bullshit!

14:55.700 --> 14:58.152
- They'll come looking for us.
- Bullshit! This is dirty money!

14:58.071 --> 15:01.238
And as far as that guy's concerned,
the cops don't even know he exists.

15:01.408 --> 15:04.195
Nobody knows about this...

15:02.875 --> 15:04.334
...but us.

15:04.369 --> 15:05.235
See there?

15:05.413 --> 15:08.663
Nobody knows but us.
It's like we came out here on a hike,

15:08.833 --> 15:11.205
and found lost treasure, right?

15:11.377 --> 15:13.703
It's the American dream
in a goddamn gym bag.

15:13.880 --> 15:16.550
He... he just wants
to walk away from it.

15:17.050 --> 15:19.044
You work for the American dream.
You don't steal it.

15:19.679 --> 15:21.802
Then this is even better.

15:25.000 --> 15:27.392
If this guy's a dope dealer, then...
like we're talkin' about...

15:27.413 --> 15:29.082
then that means we're like Robin hood.

15:29.150 --> 15:32.021
Oh, yeah, and I'll tell you what...
You got a beautiful wife at home.

15:32.193 --> 15:33.984
You're about to have a baby.

15:34.153 --> 15:36.442
I know you ain't pullin' down
that much at the feed mill.

15:37.198 --> 15:39.405
Wouldn't you love to have a piece of this?

15:39.576 --> 15:42.661
Hell, yes, I would.
But we can't just take it.

15:42.830 --> 15:45.367
Hey, what if there's a reward?
Maybe there's a reward, and they'll give...

15:45.625 --> 15:47.368
Maybe there's not!

15:48.002 --> 15:49.445
How about this...
I tell you what...

15:49.500 --> 15:52.307
I'll bet you $10,000...
just one of these packets, ...

15:52.355 --> 15:54.489
that when they find this plane, ...

15:55.594 --> 15:58.002
there's no mention of this money.

16:11.000 --> 16:16.991
Hank, why... why turn it in until we know
whether or not somebody's lookin' for it?

16:18.370 --> 16:19.484
That's right.

16:21.165 --> 16:23.739
If you scratch, then don't... don't itch.
If you... if it's...

16:24.035 --> 16:27.275
If it's broken, don't fix it.
Right?

16:27.392 --> 16:29.260
Or if you... if... if...
if the... if... if... if...

16:31.092 --> 16:32.634
And I know what you mean.

16:47.027 --> 16:49.352
Suppose I was the one to keep it?

16:51.407 --> 16:52.522
For how long?

16:52.700 --> 16:55.026
Just till spring, till they find the plane.

16:56.871 --> 16:57.951
Then what?

16:58.374 --> 17:00.000
Then, if you're right and
nobody mentions the money,

17:00.010 --> 17:02.075
we split it up, and we all leave town.

17:04.130 --> 17:05.957
Why should you get to hold it?

17:07.091 --> 17:09.927
That's the only way I'll do it.
Otherwise we can just turn it in right now.

17:09.955 --> 17:11.519
So, what, you mean...
You... you...

17:12.180 --> 17:15.799
You don't trust us?
Is that what you mean?

17:17.061 --> 17:19.184
That's a lot of money.
I guess I don't.

17:19.355 --> 17:20.834
Look, no... no promises.

17:20.835 --> 17:22.950
If somebody comes searching
for the money, I'll burn it.

17:22.913 --> 17:25.491
- Hank...
- No, that's the only way I'll do this!

17:25.510 --> 17:27.655
Look, we gotta be agreed on this.

17:27.906 --> 17:30.073
That's the deal.
That's the deal.

17:30.243 --> 17:32.504
I hold onto it,
we wait till they find the plane.

17:32.679 --> 17:35.286
If nobody mentions it,
we split it up, and we move away.

17:35.288 --> 17:36.225
OK?

17:36.541 --> 17:37.786
I'm in.

17:40.337 --> 17:41.416
We count it first.

17:45.135 --> 17:46.878
That's probably a good idea.

17:48.847 --> 17:50.222
I mean, you know...

17:51.030 --> 17:52.281
Heh heh heh...

17:52.906 --> 17:54.262
- Heh heh...
- Heh heh...

17:55.813 --> 17:58.437
This is nuts! Oh, my God!

17:59.567 --> 18:02.237
Hey, what you gonna buy, Jakey boy?

18:02.821 --> 18:04.196
I'm gonna buy me a truck.

18:04.614 --> 18:07.818
No, fuck that!
Get something classy... Trans Am!

18:07.993 --> 18:10.449
Oh, yeah, in my wildest
fuckin' dreams, a Trans Am.

18:10.521 --> 18:13.698
- You could buy a fleet of Trans Ams!
- Mary Beth!

18:13.961 --> 18:17.040
Where you been, huh?

18:36.818 --> 18:38.976
4,380,000...

18:39.153 --> 18:41.858
4,390,000...

18:42.031 --> 18:44.926
$4,400,000!

18:44.927 --> 18:47.295
Isn't that great?
Listen to that.

18:47.305 --> 18:50.790
Look at that shit, man.
Look how square it is.

18:50.959 --> 18:53.331
That is cool, huh?
How much is that apiece?

18:53.503 --> 18:54.914
About a million and...

18:55.338 --> 18:57.000
- A million and a half?
- Shh!

18:57.050 --> 18:58.000
- Shh!
- What?

18:58.087 --> 18:59.414
You hear that?

18:59.415 --> 19:00.553
Uh-uh.

19:12.953 --> 19:14.283
Oh, shit!

19:15.152 --> 19:17.561
Get in the truck, I'll handle this.

19:17.739 --> 19:19.482
Go on! Let's go!
Come on, cover up the money!

19:19.657 --> 19:22.279
Jake, get in the truck!
Dummy up! Let's go!

19:22.561 --> 19:23.708
Come on!

19:35.259 --> 19:36.338
Hey, Carl.

19:36.718 --> 19:39.257
- Engine trouble, Hank?
- Oh, I wish. Dog trouble.

19:39.596 --> 19:41.673
Jacob's mutt chased
a fox into the woods.

19:41.849 --> 19:42.763
She tree it?

19:42.934 --> 19:46.054
We thought so, but just when we went
after it, she came running back.

19:47.480 --> 19:49.390
What'd you do to your head there?

19:49.391 --> 19:53.690
Oh. God, uh...
Ran into a tree branch.

19:55.323 --> 19:59.232
- Your brother still out of work?
- Yeah.

19:59.461 --> 20:01.155
- Lou?
- Yeah, him, too.

20:01.789 --> 20:03.496
That's a shame, ain't it?

20:04.291 --> 20:06.331
Well, we probably better be heading back...

20:08.138 --> 20:10.795
- Hey, hello, Jacob!
- Hey, Carl, how you doin'?

20:10.965 --> 20:12.294
Good, good.

20:12.417 --> 20:15.056
I was beginning to think
you were trying to avoid me.

20:15.271 --> 20:16.716
I'm sorry?

20:16.889 --> 20:18.965
Well, you sittin' over there in that truck.

20:19.141 --> 20:20.849
I thought you was trying to avoid me.

20:21.018 --> 20:23.018
No, I was just sittin' in the truck.

20:23.115 --> 20:26.258
It's a little cold out here, you know.
Just keepin' warm.

20:26.817 --> 20:28.800
Well, we probably better be...

20:28.900 --> 20:31.195
Did you tell him about the plane?

20:31.196 --> 20:33.189
- It sou-sounded like a plane.
- What plane?

20:37.704 --> 20:39.247
What, you heard a plane?

20:40.540 --> 20:42.949
I don't know what he heard.
You know he's always hearing shit.

20:43.127 --> 20:45.249
Maybe you better tell me, Jacob.

20:45.420 --> 20:47.663
No, that's OK.
We're gonna get on home.

20:47.836 --> 20:49.067
- All right.
- All right.

20:49.090 --> 20:51.089
Come on, man!
It's New Year's, let's get outta here!

20:51.406 --> 20:52.753
Call me, Carl.
Happy New Year!

20:52.971 --> 20:55.806
- Sure you don't need any help?
- No, we're all set. Thanks.

20:55.900 --> 20:56.592
All right.

20:57.059 --> 21:00.096
Goddamn it! I've seen you do
some pretty stupid things, Jacob.

21:00.271 --> 21:02.477
But that pretty much takes the cake!

21:02.857 --> 21:05.395
- It was my idea.
- Oh, well, that's brilliant, Lou.

21:05.568 --> 21:07.894
Now when they find the plane,
and they realize the money's gone,

21:08.071 --> 21:10.112
they'll know right off who took it.

21:11.200 --> 21:13.442
Well, that's... that's what's
cool about it, though.

21:13.620 --> 21:17.155
I mean, we wouldn't tell somebody
if we were the ones that did it.

21:17.332 --> 21:19.787
It's not like he said that you actually
saw a plane going down.

21:19.959 --> 21:22.202
Just you thought you might've
heard one with engine trouble.

21:22.379 --> 21:24.253
You want me to burn the money?!

21:24.799 --> 21:26.590
I am not going to prison over this!

21:26.759 --> 21:29.333
If it looks like there's even the slightest
chance of us getting caught,

21:29.512 --> 21:33.380
I swear to God, it's all gonna vanish!
You understand?

21:43.861 --> 21:47.638
"It was a pine apple."
Ha ha ha...

21:59.046 --> 22:02.289
Oh, God...
This is gonna be fun.

22:04.134 --> 22:06.200
Where the hell have you been?!

22:06.400 --> 22:10.072
You always come when I'm finished.
I'm finished, you asshole!

22:12.978 --> 22:13.760
Hey, Nancy!

22:15.498 --> 22:17.308
Don't... Don't hit...
Don't hit Mary Beth.

22:17.608 --> 22:20.182
Remember, nobody knows about this.
That includes Nancy.

22:20.436 --> 22:22.655
She's gonna have to find out
about it sooner or later.

22:22.700 --> 22:24.530
She's gonna wonder where all
the money's coming from.

22:24.690 --> 22:25.744
2 hours late!

22:25.960 --> 22:26.644
Stop it!

22:26.750 --> 22:29.982
Tell her when we decide
it's safe to keep it, but not before then.

22:30.706 --> 22:31.952
Then the same goes for Sarah.

22:33.126 --> 22:34.288
Of course.

22:35.295 --> 22:35.959
Damn it!

22:36.129 --> 22:40.627
Come on! You promised to shovel
the walk, you lazy son of a bitch!

22:40.801 --> 22:42.800
Calm down, baby!
I got a good reason for being late.

22:42.899 --> 22:43.899
What?

22:44.050 --> 22:45.127
See you, Lou!

22:49.061 --> 22:50.934
You know, I bet he's telling her.

22:52.021 --> 22:53.516
That guy can't keep a secret.

23:06.900 --> 23:08.401
- Hey, honey.
- Hey.

23:09.792 --> 23:10.823
Where you been?

23:17.717 --> 23:19.093
I was starting to get worried about you.

23:19.260 --> 23:21.630
- Sorry I'm late.
- Oh, that's all right.

23:21.633 --> 23:22.970
Hey!

23:22.973 --> 23:24.384
What happened to your head?

23:24.559 --> 23:27.180
- It's OK. It's just a scratch.
- It's all bloody.

23:28.313 --> 23:29.808
Can I ask you something?

23:30.200 --> 23:31.310
Yeah, sure.

23:33.068 --> 23:34.527
What if you were walking in the woods...

23:34.695 --> 23:35.893
It's not deep.

23:36.071 --> 23:38.195
And you found a bag full of money,

23:38.866 --> 23:42.995
let's say $4 million...
Would you keep it?

23:44.289 --> 23:46.282
Of course not.
Here, hold that.

23:46.458 --> 23:47.538
How come?

23:47.710 --> 23:50.462
Well, for starters, it'd be stealing.

23:50.630 --> 23:53.916
We were talking about lost money here,
nobody's looking for it.

23:57.388 --> 23:59.795
- $4 million of lost money...
- Yeah.

24:00.056 --> 24:01.635
- that nobody's looking for?
- Yeah.

24:03.811 --> 24:05.934
Well, so then whose money is it?

24:06.230 --> 24:07.226
Yours.

24:07.250 --> 24:08.250
Oh!

24:09.248 --> 24:10.291
Ooh!

24:11.612 --> 24:15.480
It's my money?
But whose money was it before?

24:15.866 --> 24:17.408
A bank robber's.

24:18.620 --> 24:20.411
So then it's the bank's money.

24:21.581 --> 24:25.033
All right, it's, uh, a drug dealer's.

24:28.600 --> 24:29.700
Hank.

24:30.966 --> 24:32.600
I mean, this is really silly.

24:32.700 --> 24:34.668
Obviously you want me to say
something in particular.

24:34.847 --> 24:37.698
I don't know what it is, but you
want me to agree with you or say

24:37.700 --> 24:40.637
that you're right or something.
But I wouldn't take it.

24:40.811 --> 24:42.603
That's just me. I wouldn't.

24:58.205 --> 24:59.404
It's real.

25:12.222 --> 25:15.139
If we keep it, we never have to
worry about money again.

25:16.060 --> 25:18.550
But we don't have to worry
about money now, Hank.

25:19.020 --> 25:20.681
You've got a good job.

25:21.190 --> 25:22.601
We don't need it.

25:23.443 --> 25:26.444
Yeah, but nobody gets
hurt by us keeping it.

25:29.283 --> 25:33.363
I mean, that's what makes it a crime,
doesn't it? Somebody getting hurt?

25:33.663 --> 25:35.702
What makes it a crime
is that it's against the law.

25:35.773 --> 25:37.823
It doesn't matter if somebody
gets hurt or if they don't.

25:37.990 --> 25:40.590
- If you get caught, then you go to jail.
- Nobody's gonna get caught.

25:40.700 --> 25:43.150
The money's the only evidence
that we've done anything wrong.

25:44.049 --> 25:47.253
We sit on it, we see what happens.

25:47.428 --> 25:51.509
If somebody comes searching for it,
then we just burn it and that will be that.

25:51.808 --> 25:54.478
There's no risk.
We'll always be in control.

25:55.270 --> 25:56.979
What about Jacob and Lou?

25:57.148 --> 26:00.683
As long as we're handling the money
they have to let us call the shots.

26:02.278 --> 26:07.522
It seems... crazy just to give it up.

26:07.784 --> 26:10.323
I mean, before we know if
anybody's searching for it.

26:13.165 --> 26:15.703
This is it.
It ain't champagne, but...

26:17.170 --> 26:18.545
Happy New Year!

26:29.934 --> 26:32.556
You have to go back and
return some of the money.

26:33.726 --> 26:34.968
What?

26:36.066 --> 26:39.601
A lot. Like 500,000.

26:40.321 --> 26:44.402
You see, that way when they find the plane
they'll assume nobody's been there yet.

26:44.576 --> 26:46.568
It will put us beyond suspicion.

26:46.745 --> 26:48.568
No one would walk away
from that much money...

26:48.658 --> 26:49.897
Wait a second!

26:51.459 --> 26:52.573
We're gonna keep the rest?

26:53.210 --> 26:57.078
You'll have to go in the morning
so when it storms later it'll cover your tracks.

26:58.258 --> 26:59.421
You can't tell Jacob though.

27:00.343 --> 27:01.838
What, do you think
he'd go back and take it?

27:04.097 --> 27:05.889
It's... it's just being careful.

27:06.517 --> 27:09.091
That's what we have to be from now on.
We have to be careful.

27:09.270 --> 27:11.144
We have to be thinking ahead all the time.

27:12.936 --> 27:15.379
OK. OK.

27:19.253 --> 27:20.296
OK.

27:40.233 --> 27:41.475
Jacob!

27:44.643 --> 27:46.683
Jacob, come on, open up!

27:53.362 --> 27:55.745
Hey, I screwed up,
I moved the pilot.

27:55.845 --> 27:58.494
Come on, we gotta go put
him back like he was.

27:59.702 --> 28:01.446
Come on, I need a lookout.

28:17.014 --> 28:20.200
If somebody comes by,
you pretend you're changing the tire.

28:24.647 --> 28:26.604
You know, that's not gonna work.

28:27.233 --> 28:28.312
What do you mean,
it's not gonna work?

28:28.693 --> 28:30.567
Nobody's gonna believe that.
It's not flat.

28:34.783 --> 28:36.361
You're kinda crafty.

28:38.246 --> 28:39.740
I observe things.

28:40.414 --> 28:43.838
Observe and learn, my friend.
Observe and learn.

28:52.011 --> 28:53.209
That's cool.

29:55.082 --> 29:56.956
Jacob, what happened,
she die on you?

29:57.126 --> 29:58.856
No, we had a flat.
We had a flat tire.

29:59.087 --> 30:01.800
I fixed it. See?
The new one's on there now.

30:01.925 --> 30:04.126
I took the other one,
the bad one, and put it in the trunk.

30:04.235 --> 30:05.910
It's back there now,
flat as a pancake.

30:06.020 --> 30:07.536
But it's cool now.
Everything's all right.

30:07.680 --> 30:10.847
You see that God damned fox
come by here about 5 minutes ago

30:11.017 --> 30:12.475
heading right on down
to the woods?

30:12.811 --> 30:15.950
No, I didn't see a fox.
I didn't see any fox.

30:16.106 --> 30:18.913
Well, if you'd been standing where
I'm sitting he'd have bit you on the ass.

30:35.194 --> 30:36.536
Why don't you stay here?

30:36.694 --> 30:37.736
Hey, Hank!

30:42.427 --> 30:44.586
Don't do anything stupid.

30:48.655 --> 30:49.893
Jacob!

30:52.000 --> 30:53.541
Oh, God...

30:53.741 --> 30:55.899
Jesus, Jacob, what the fuck?!

30:56.361 --> 30:59.104
I... I... I... I hit...
I hit the farmer.

30:59.613 --> 31:02.091
- He was tracking a fox. I... I...
- Dwight!

31:02.206 --> 31:04.000
He was gonna go right by the plane.
I had to do something.

31:04.082 --> 31:05.700
I was just trying to help us out.

31:05.870 --> 31:09.536
Just listen... listen to his...
to his heart or something like that.

31:09.219 --> 31:10.992
Come on, man, listen.
You gotta do it... you...

31:11.752 --> 31:12.701
He's... he's gonna be OK.

31:13.170 --> 31:15.210
Oh, God, Jacob,
I think you killed him.

31:15.381 --> 31:18.358
I'm pretty sure he's gonna be OK.
What else was I gonna do?

31:18.760 --> 31:20.551
Oh, God. He's dead.

31:20.720 --> 31:22.843
Oh, Hank, that's not right.

31:25.170 --> 31:26.942
No, we could probably...
We could probably do...

31:28.229 --> 31:30.471
We can probably do that CPR deal.

31:30.648 --> 31:33.685
And you know, you could do that, uh,
cardiac arrest thing, couldn't you?

31:33.860 --> 31:35.403
We could do something,
goddamn it!

31:35.571 --> 31:37.065
Jacob, what the hell you doing?

31:37.148 --> 31:38.898
- Stop it!
- Come on!

31:38.990 --> 31:40.353
I'm working CPR!

31:40.554 --> 31:41.655
Goddamn it, stop it!

31:41.800 --> 31:42.800
Come on! Come on!

31:42.912 --> 31:46.862
Be still. Let me think.
OK, we can't panic.

31:47.792 --> 31:49.406
Have any cars gone by?

31:49.407 --> 31:51.935
- Uh, cars?
- Cars, cars, come on, think.

31:51.950 --> 31:53.573
While I was in the woods,
you see any cars go by?

31:53.674 --> 31:54.374
Why, Hank?

31:56.197 --> 31:57.297
Oh, God.

31:57.451 --> 31:58.923
All right.

31:59.306 --> 32:00.681
We gotta make this look
like it was an accident.

32:00.506 --> 32:02.081
- Come on.
- An accident?

32:04.000 --> 32:05.426
Grab his legs.

32:07.314 --> 32:09.806
Wait, wait, wait.
We can't do that.

32:09.984 --> 32:11.552
What do you mean we can't do it?

32:11.694 --> 32:14.541
Because we're gonna make tracks and
they're gonna see them and follow 'em.

32:14.550 --> 32:16.551
It's gonna be like a
crime scene or something.

32:16.650 --> 32:18.575
We're gonna drive the car
back to the bridge.

32:18.744 --> 32:20.571
I'll put him on the snowmobile
and take him through the park.

32:21.288 --> 32:23.827
You gotta get there ahead of me.

32:22.453 --> 32:24.331
So whatever you do,
I don't want you to stop.

32:24.000 --> 32:26.289
I want you to just drive
on by then circle back.

32:25.790 --> 32:27.041
I don't want people to
see you sitting there.

32:26.461 --> 32:28.750
- Circle back?
- That's right.

32:27.876 --> 32:29.075
That's right.

32:29.076 --> 32:30.430
Come on, come on now.

32:32.927 --> 32:34.801
They're not gonna take me away, are they?
I mean, you gotta promise me...

32:34.970 --> 32:37.592
Nobody's gonna take you away,
I promise. But we gotta hurry.

32:37.765 --> 32:38.761
It's gonna be OK, right, Hank?

32:38.933 --> 32:40.345
Come on, we gotta go.

32:40.519 --> 32:43.100
- You gonna be there, right?
- I'm gonna be there. Now just go!

32:43.359 --> 32:44.437
Go!

33:22.774 --> 33:23.890
Dwight?

33:26.902 --> 33:28.351
Dwight!

33:28.573 --> 33:29.901
Your brother.

33:31.451 --> 33:32.826
He hit me.

33:36.456 --> 33:37.620
You call the police.

33:40.962 --> 33:42.540
Get the police.

35:38.094 --> 35:40.502
Jacob, what are you doing?
Come on, before anybody sees!

35:40.680 --> 35:42.340
- I'm not gonna do this.
- What?

35:42.515 --> 35:45.137
Well, it's just stupid. I mean, if...
See, if we cover it up

35:45.310 --> 35:48.347
it's just gonna be worse anyhow.
So, you know, I'm... I'm just...

35:48.401 --> 35:48.922
Get in the car!

35:49.064 --> 35:52.149
I'm just gonna go and pull him out, you know?
We're just gonna tell everybody the truth.

35:52.610 --> 35:55.149
Just gonna tell 'em about the money
and everything and just say that I... that I...

35:55.322 --> 35:57.778
- You're gonna leave tracks!
- Wait a minute.

35:58.450 --> 36:00.608
This is my decision!

36:00.649 --> 36:01.786
Mine!

36:01.787 --> 36:03.198
Not yours!

36:08.712 --> 36:10.336
You didn't kill him.

36:17.096 --> 36:18.805
We both did.

36:21.058 --> 36:22.719
What are you talking about, Hank?

36:26.273 --> 36:30.223
He was alive when you left.
I smothered him.

36:31.821 --> 36:34.110
I guess that makes it my decision.

36:54.847 --> 36:57.469
It's gonna be OK.
I mean, it looked real.

36:57.642 --> 37:01.971
And even if... I mean, let's say it didn't
look like an accident. Whatever. I mean...

37:02.773 --> 37:04.183
Why would anyone think of us?

37:04.358 --> 37:06.232
Your tracks lead right to the plane.

37:06.986 --> 37:09.987
But it's gonna snow! Any minute now,
it's gonna start snowing.

37:10.156 --> 37:11.615
Was there any blood?

37:12.241 --> 37:12.906
Blood?

37:13.160 --> 37:16.861
Jacob hit him.
Was there blood anywhere?

37:14.875 --> 37:17.230
Did he get blood on anything?
Was there blood on the road or...

37:17.328 --> 37:18.244
I don't remember.

37:18.415 --> 37:20.325
- Did you look?
- I looked, but I... I just don't...

37:20.501 --> 37:22.540
I mean, it was all hap...

37:23.713 --> 37:27.289
Honey, it's gonna snow. It's gonna snow
and everything's gonna be covered up.

37:27.300 --> 37:29.991
- All the tracks...
- Shh.

37:30.554 --> 37:32.962
<i>He was apparently trying to cross
along this bank of snow.</i>

37:33.141 --> 37:35.809
<i>when his snowmobile slipped over the edge</i>

37:35.976 --> 37:39.511
<i>throwing him into the icy
waters of Anders creek.</i>

37:39.689 --> 37:44.767
<i>Wright county deputies recovered the body
shortly before 4:00 this afternoon.</i>

37:44.945 --> 37:49.323
<i>A tragic beginning to this new year
for one local family.</i>

37:49.700 --> 37:51.195
<i>Back to you, Paul.</i>

37:51.196 --> 37:52.395
<i>Thanks, Tracy.</i>

37:59.211 --> 38:01.750
I wish you hadn't told Jacob.

38:03.466 --> 38:05.044
I wish he still thought that he did it.

38:05.969 --> 38:06.799
Does it scare you?

38:07.137 --> 38:08.964
Yeah, it scares me.
What if he tells somebody?

38:09.139 --> 38:10.135
I mean, what I did.

38:11.934 --> 38:13.262
What you did?

38:13.600 --> 38:17.646
Well, I know that you only did it
because you felt trapped, ...

38:16.382 --> 38:18.467
that you couldn't find any other way.

38:18.620 --> 38:22.992
Would you have done the same thing?
I mean, if you'd been there instead of me?

38:26.084 --> 38:28.907
I... I...
I just need to know if it's possible.

38:32.177 --> 38:33.324
Oh, honey!

38:50.644 --> 38:52.476
You listening to me, Hank?

38:52.544 --> 38:56.900
Every Monday I come down here,
buy 2 bags of feed, regular as clock work.

38:57.193 --> 39:02.350
2 bags of wheat, 4 times a month.
That's 8 bags I'm supposed to be billed for.

39:02.400 --> 39:06.152
- I don't know how else to get through to you.
- December started on a Monday, Mr. Schmitt.

39:06.170 --> 39:08.000
So there were 5 mondays in the month.
So you came in here 5...

39:08.080 --> 39:10.453
Are you telling me there were
5 weeks last month?

39:10.625 --> 39:13.579
No, sir, I'm telling you
there were 5 Mondays. Excuse me.

39:14.838 --> 39:15.669
I got it.

39:15.700 --> 39:16.631
Yeah.

39:16.632 --> 39:18.209
<i>Hey, Hank, it's me.</i>

39:18.717 --> 39:20.093
Hang on a second.

39:20.595 --> 39:23.051
Listen, check that calendar over there
if you don't believe me, sir.

39:23.223 --> 39:24.302
<i>I need to talk to you.</i>

39:24.474 --> 39:26.763
Well, I'm a little busy right now, Jacob.
What is it?

39:26.935 --> 39:29.225
<i>OK, listen,
can you meet me at the farm?</i>

39:29.689 --> 39:31.017
- What farm?
<i>- Our farm.</i>

39:32.107 --> 39:33.851
Look, uh, what is it?

39:34.026 --> 39:36.518
<i>On your lunch break.
12:30, OK?</i>

39:36.863 --> 39:39.105
Hey, are we straight on this, Mr. Schmitt?

39:40.034 --> 39:41.444
Thanks for coming in.

39:43.079 --> 39:44.988
Look, I can't drive out there right...

39:45.100 --> 39:46.188
Jacob?

40:09.738 --> 40:10.881
Jacob?

40:12.405 --> 40:14.982
Hey, what are you doing here?

40:15.070 --> 40:17.521
Look out!
Ha ha ha ha ha.

40:17.868 --> 40:20.359
- What the hell'd you drag me out here for?
- Listen to this. I'm gonna buy it back.

40:20.871 --> 40:24.454
I'm gonna fix it up. I'm gonna rebuild it
just like it was before mom and dad died.

40:24.667 --> 40:26.787
Whoa, whoa. Come on, wait, wait.
We've been through all this.

40:26.794 --> 40:31.540
We've been over this. Once we split up
the money, we've gotta leave. We have to go.

40:33.677 --> 40:38.055
What do you... what do you want me to do,
just like that, just drive off by myself?

40:40.000 --> 40:41.600
Well, I mean, suppose you stay...

40:41.720 --> 40:43.583
Where are you gonna tell
people you got the money?

40:43.675 --> 40:44.900
Oh, that's easy.

40:45.000 --> 40:49.200
We just tell people that Sarah
inherited some money. It's easy.

40:49.320 --> 40:52.155
You know, nobody around here
knows anything about her family.

40:53.157 --> 40:57.986
You guys could've just bought the farm,
you know, and then left me to run it.

40:58.163 --> 41:00.571
- It's not gonna work.
- I thought this was gonna make you happy.

41:00.842 --> 41:02.184
Jacob...

41:03.669 --> 41:05.828
Farming? Come on.

41:07.215 --> 41:11.165
You don't just buy a farm.
You gotta... you gotta work it.

41:11.470 --> 41:13.925
You gotta know about machinery and seed.

41:14.097 --> 41:15.473
- I know that.
- No, you don't.

41:15.641 --> 41:20.242
Fertilizers, pesticides, herbicides,
drainage, irrigation, the weather?

41:20.300 --> 41:22.724
Come on, you don't know
about any of that stuff.

41:22.899 --> 41:24.975
You're gonna end up just like dad!

41:25.528 --> 41:26.808
Why do you think he ended up like that?

41:26.987 --> 41:29.146
I'll tell you how he ended up like that.

41:29.323 --> 41:32.775
He had 2 mortgages riding on the place.
He couldn't make the payments.

41:32.952 --> 41:35.526
- Where do you think the money went?
- He was a bad businessman.

41:35.706 --> 41:39.289
Where do you think the money went?
No, you think he spent it all on the farm?

41:39.460 --> 41:42.664
I'll tell you exactly where the money went:
4 years of college, bud!

41:44.215 --> 41:46.341
Yeah, or didn't you ever think
about how he paid for that?

41:46.655 --> 41:49.213
- Didn't that ever occur to you?
- No, my tuition was...

41:49.323 --> 41:51.885
Listen, I'm supposed to get the farm!

41:53.734 --> 41:57.635
What do I get?!
I'm supposed to get the farm.

41:59.433 --> 42:02.800
Jacob, you got... you got...
the whole world. You can...

42:03.062 --> 42:05.069
I don't wanna hear that.

42:10.795 --> 42:12.988
You can go anywhere you want.

42:16.494 --> 42:18.153
This is what I want.

42:20.373 --> 42:22.661
This is... this is where
I wanna be.

42:24.085 --> 42:25.745
It's my home, Hank.

42:47.706 --> 42:48.749
Shit.

43:06.049 --> 43:07.248
- Hey, honey.
- What?

43:07.426 --> 43:09.751
I wanna show you something.

43:12.058 --> 43:13.205
- What is it?
- I got this...

43:13.300 --> 43:16.013
I had it sent over
from the other branch.

43:16.352 --> 43:17.182
Look, here it is.

43:17.729 --> 43:19.805
"Heiress's body ID'd by feds."

43:19.981 --> 43:22.224
"$4.4 million ransom."

43:22.651 --> 43:27.444
You see? This person nobody knows
has just disappeared right into thin air.

43:28.575 --> 43:30.282
Do you recognize one
of them from the plane?

43:30.451 --> 43:31.781
I can't tell.

43:32.287 --> 43:34.078
His face was...

43:38.000 --> 43:39.100
What?

43:39.257 --> 43:40.831
This changes it.

43:40.900 --> 43:42.120
Why is that?

43:43.550 --> 43:45.542
We can't say it isn't stealing anymore.

43:47.229 --> 43:50.894
Well, Hank, it's always been stealing.
We just didn't know who we were stealing from.

43:51.150 --> 43:54.203
We thought it was drug money.
We thought it was money that we could find...

43:54.233 --> 43:56.875
- No, you thought that. This is good. I'm glad...
- It's good?

43:57.000 --> 43:59.860
Yes, it's good we know where it's from,
because I was starting to get worried.

43:59.990 --> 44:02.689
I thought that it might
be counterfeit or marked.

44:02.850 --> 44:04.856
- It might still be marked.
- No, it says right here.

44:05.200 --> 44:09.114
Look: "denomination in unmarked bills".
Unmarked, you see?

44:11.748 --> 44:15.918
You're just being paranoid, Hank.
It's over. It's good.

44:16.474 --> 44:18.142
Sarah?

44:18.714 --> 44:20.043
Would you come here, please?

44:20.216 --> 44:22.340
Sure. OK, just a second.

44:22.636 --> 44:24.260
I'll see you tonight.

45:21.013 --> 45:22.100
Ha ha ha ha ha.

45:23.000 --> 45:24.000
Jesus!

45:24.100 --> 45:25.787
Hey, come on, Hank!
Open up!

45:26.600 --> 45:30.150
- What the hell are you doing?
- Hey, "Mr. Accountant"!

45:30.165 --> 45:32.000
Well, I've come to make a tiny withdrawal.

45:32.100 --> 45:34.000
Go home.
Turn around and go home right now.

45:34.142 --> 45:37.550
- Oh, come on! It's freezing out here, Hank!
- Shh! Keep it down!

45:37.887 --> 45:39.381
All right, just for a second.

45:42.559 --> 45:45.845
I don't have time for this shit.
I gotta get up and go to work.

45:46.605 --> 45:48.065
I want my share.

45:48.180 --> 45:49.269
What?

45:49.400 --> 45:51.559
I do. I want my share.

45:53.238 --> 45:56.400
I don't have the money here,
and even if I did, I wouldn't give you any.

45:56.500 --> 45:57.600
Oh, come on, now.

45:57.690 --> 46:00.483
Look, just because you have it
doesn't mean it's yours.

46:01.038 --> 46:03.161
Part of that is my money.

46:04.041 --> 46:06.367
Part of it might be your money...

46:07.211 --> 46:09.169
If we decide to keep it.

46:09.339 --> 46:12.251
The plan was to sit on the money
till we decide that it's safe to keep it.

46:12.300 --> 46:14.950
- Why are you coming over here with this shit?
- All right, look. I'll tell you what.

46:15.054 --> 46:18.138
Just give me one packet, OK?

46:18.342 --> 46:23.220
Just one packet.
And I'll come back later for the rest.

46:24.940 --> 46:28.024
Ask me again, and I'll go
burn it tomorrow morning.

46:28.402 --> 46:29.731
Is that clear?

46:32.491 --> 46:33.491
It's a bluff.

46:33.550 --> 46:34.739
What?

46:34.835 --> 46:38.435
Yeah, it's a bluff!
B-L-U-F-F.

46:38.663 --> 46:42.080
Oh, then why don't you call it then
and just see what happens?

46:42.807 --> 46:44.257
- Yeah.
- All right. OK.

46:45.046 --> 46:48.545
See, Jacob told me a little secret,
"Mr. Accountant".

46:50.010 --> 46:53.545
I know what happened to Dwight Stephanson.

46:57.560 --> 46:59.435
You drank too much.

46:59.605 --> 47:01.597
I want one of those packets!

47:03.526 --> 47:08.000
I told you, I don't have the money here.
I hid it away from the house.

47:08.100 --> 47:11.950
Mm-hmm. Well, you know what?
It'd be a shame if somebody was to

47:12.000 --> 47:14.340
drop a note to Carl Jenkins saying

47:14.370 --> 47:18.960
there might just be a little something
suspicious about Dwight Stephanson's accident.

47:19.001 --> 47:22.951
He just drove off that bridge?
Do you believe that? Do you?!

47:23.131 --> 47:25.088
Come on. Jesus, Lou!

47:25.383 --> 47:28.171
Remember, you're a thief, too.

47:28.637 --> 47:32.302
We're all in this together.
If one of us goes to jail, we all do.

47:45.340 --> 47:46.382
Oh, God.

47:50.244 --> 47:52.487
I need my share, Hank.

47:53.289 --> 47:54.405
I do.

47:55.834 --> 47:57.294
I'm broke...

47:58.546 --> 48:00.337
And I owe people money.

48:03.546 --> 48:07.190
- Christ, Lou, I mean wh-wh...
- I need some help here, man.

48:09.516 --> 48:11.095
OK, just wait here.

48:28.269 --> 48:29.916
Here, here.

48:31.417 --> 48:32.365
40 dollars?

48:32.751 --> 48:34.411
Shh! That's all I got.

48:34.627 --> 48:37.795
Maybe I can go to the bank
and get you a loan out of our savings.

48:38.092 --> 48:42.169
Look, look, look.
The money's a day's drive from here.

48:42.345 --> 48:45.263
Even if I wanted go get it, I can't go get it,
not till Sarah has the baby.

48:45.432 --> 48:46.463
A day's drive?!

48:47.059 --> 48:51.093
Yeah, that's right. I put it in a storage locker
above the interstate.

48:51.388 --> 48:55.925
- What the hell is it doing in a storage...
- Shh! It's safe. Don't worry, all right?

48:56.269 --> 48:58.559
I didn't want it near us in case
we come under any suspicion.

48:58.731 --> 49:01.056
- How the hell's that gonna happen?
- How's that gonna happen?

49:01.233 --> 49:04.819
How about Carl knowing about
the plane, huh? Who's idea was that?

49:07.905 --> 49:08.948
Yeah.

49:09.105 --> 49:10.148
All right.

49:11.953 --> 49:17.861
But we go get it as soon as she's done,
split it up right there...

49:18.250 --> 49:19.494
Right?

49:23.409 --> 49:24.451
Yeah.

49:31.853 --> 49:33.000
Hank...

49:34.565 --> 49:39.234
# Skippy and Buddy...
# Skippy and Buddy...

49:44.199 --> 49:46.211
Hey, I said whoa.

49:46.399 --> 49:50.611
I'm looking for Hank and Sarah.
I'm sorry.

49:53.735 --> 49:55.063
Oh, God, look at this.

49:57.213 --> 50:00.001
Do you have a car seat in the car
you'll be traveling home in?

50:00.467 --> 50:01.795
Is it currently installed?

50:01.968 --> 50:03.594
Hello, look who's here!

50:04.888 --> 50:07.925
Bearing tidings and gifts and great joy.

50:08.100 --> 50:09.263
Would you sign here?

50:09.685 --> 50:11.457
Sure.

50:11.813 --> 50:13.687
What do you mean "gambling"?
Where?

50:13.857 --> 50:15.399
At the casino. He lost some money.

50:15.567 --> 50:17.856
- How much?
- I don't know how much.

50:17.990 --> 50:19.172
Shh!

50:19.238 --> 50:21.019
- Hey, congratulations!
- Thank you.

50:21.464 --> 50:22.714
Did you see that little baby?

50:22.575 --> 50:24.449
It looked like a little tomato.

50:24.619 --> 50:27.905
How could you have told him that, huh?

50:28.624 --> 50:31.910
I put myself out for you.
What do you do, you betray me?

50:32.086 --> 50:32.999
What are you talking about?

50:33.170 --> 50:36.207
What am I talking about?
It's like there's two sides now.

50:36.716 --> 50:40.500
Why are you both always talking
about sides? There's no sides.

50:40.678 --> 50:42.054
Who's talking about sides?

50:42.723 --> 50:46.057
I'm on both of your sides.
We're all in this together, man.

50:46.227 --> 50:49.562
If you had to pick right now,
who'd it be?

50:49.750 --> 50:51.521
No, I don't...
why would I wanna pick?

50:51.700 --> 50:52.940
No, I wanna know...

50:53.710 --> 50:55.356
Me or Lou?

51:05.916 --> 51:07.789
Good grief, man. I...

51:09.461 --> 51:11.455
I'd pick you.
You're my brother.

51:29.234 --> 51:31.903
I bou... I bought
a present for the baby.

51:35.031 --> 51:38.566
OK... OK, I... I brought it from the house.
I didn't buy it, but, look, it's...

51:39.912 --> 51:41.914
It's kinda cool.
Just trust me on this one.

51:42.000 --> 51:44.874
You're gonna like it, I think,
when you see what it is.

51:53.424 --> 51:54.467
Thanks.

52:04.440 --> 52:06.813
- God, it's used.
- Let me see that.

52:08.403 --> 52:10.362
Oh, my gosh, this was his...

52:10.655 --> 52:12.280
when we were kids.

52:13.284 --> 52:14.943
Oh, I guess it's sweet
of him then, isn't it?

52:15.118 --> 52:16.613
Buddy the bear.

52:16.954 --> 52:18.532
Here's your little girl.

52:22.502 --> 52:23.761
Oh, good, good, good.

52:24.671 --> 52:27.756
Got her?
She's just about ready for her feeding.

52:27.925 --> 52:29.502
Would you grab that thing?

52:29.503 --> 52:32.002
Thank you so much.
Thank you.

52:33.890 --> 52:35.966
Hello, little girl.

52:37.090 --> 52:38.166
Hello.

52:39.104 --> 52:40.433
She's hungry.

52:48.156 --> 52:50.778
I want you to buy one of
those little tape recorders.

52:51.034 --> 52:53.821
You know, the little dictating kind,
the kind you can hide in your pocket?

52:54.080 --> 52:55.360
Why do you want a tape recorder?

52:55.831 --> 52:57.955
You're gonna tape Lou
confessing to Stephanson's murder.

52:58.501 --> 53:00.125
What?
What are you talking about?

53:06.635 --> 53:10.633
You and Jacob invite him out for drinks.
Get him drunk.

53:11.266 --> 53:13.222
You take him back to his place.

53:13.392 --> 53:17.477
Then you start joking around,
kidding about confessing to the police.

53:17.520 --> 53:20.016
Each of you takes a turn
pretending how you'd do it.

53:20.359 --> 53:21.937
You go first,

53:23.154 --> 53:26.751
Jacob second, and Lou last.
And when Lou goes, you tape him.

53:28.327 --> 53:29.607
Come on, that's not gonna work.

53:29.786 --> 53:32.263
Jacob helps you.
That's the key.

53:32.706 --> 53:34.996
If Jacob eggs him on, he'll do it.

53:35.168 --> 53:39.379
Yeah, but even if he, you know, even if he
talks on the tape, it won't mean anything.

53:39.547 --> 53:41.504
I mean, who's ever gonna believe it?

53:41.884 --> 53:45.716
Well, it doesn't matter
as long as Lou believes it,

53:46.096 --> 53:48.718
as long as he sees that
Jacob's taking your side.

53:49.684 --> 53:51.094
That's all you want.

53:54.022 --> 53:56.394
We should at least try,
shouldn't we?

53:56.566 --> 53:59.058
We can't lose anything by trying...

54:00.058 --> 54:01.457
Right?

54:02.657 --> 54:04.558
Come on, it's not like
I'm asking you to do that much.

54:04.575 --> 54:06.278
Here, just pick up the phone
and give him a call and say:

54:06.350 --> 54:08.200
"Hey, Lou, Hank suggested we go out
drinking." tomorrow night."

54:08.496 --> 54:11.248
Hank suggested we go out drinking?
What are talking about?

54:11.416 --> 54:14.204
- Will you let me finish?
- We suggest we go out drinking.

54:12.616 --> 54:15.420
- You don't ever suggest we go out drinking.
- I'm getting to that. Let me finish.

54:15.500 --> 54:17.000
I'm saying:

54:17.150 --> 54:19.206
Tell him I've agreed to split up the money.

54:19.384 --> 54:22.420
I thought it'd be a good idea for us to...
to go out and celebrate first.

54:22.721 --> 54:25.638
So you want me to trick him?
You want me to trick Lou?

54:25.097 --> 54:26.765
You want me to trick my friend?
OK.

54:26.809 --> 54:28.600
Do you get what's happening here?

54:29.311 --> 54:31.139
Do you understand the seriousness
of the situation we're in?

54:31.314 --> 54:34.648
- He can put us both in jail, Jacob.
- He's not gonna send us to jail.

54:34.901 --> 54:39.563
Well, I can't take that chance,
not now, not with the baby.

54:40.783 --> 54:42.775
I can't afford to go to prison, Jacob.

54:42.993 --> 54:45.236
I mean, wh-what about Sarah, huh?

54:46.455 --> 54:47.915
Wh-what are they gonna do?

54:50.628 --> 54:52.627
I'm gonna have to get rid of that
Christmas tree out of here.

54:52.651 --> 54:54.379
It's too dry. It's gonna start a fire...

54:54.458 --> 54:57.004
Would you pay attention here?
Pay attention!

54:57.261 --> 55:01.381
- What would dad do?
- I'll think about it.

54:58.978 --> 55:00.436
Don't do that, please, Hank.

55:00.500 --> 55:02.336
Don't you think he'd
want us to stick together?

55:02.450 --> 55:06.895
Don't say that. I mean, you don't
know what the hell dad would do.

55:04.556 --> 55:07.225
That's fucked up.
Don't bring him up.

55:17.967 --> 55:19.109
Well...

55:20.452 --> 55:24.285
What if I was to say I'd help you
get the farm back, huh?

55:28.985 --> 55:30.463
All right...

55:31.507 --> 55:33.713
I'll help you buy back the farm.

55:35.845 --> 55:37.838
But you got to help me first.

55:46.273 --> 55:48.979
You know, all I meant by that
about the tree is it's just dried out.

55:49.000 --> 55:52.737
And it could start a fucking fire.
You know how that stuff goes.

55:53.000 --> 55:56.548
It wasn't like I was trying to ignore you
or something like that.

55:56.618 --> 55:59.906
I was just, you know, I was talking about
practical shit to you is all it was.

56:13.137 --> 56:16.506
Yeah, we got that white carpet.

56:18.229 --> 56:19.876
- Honey?
- Oh. Oh, hey.

56:19.980 --> 56:20.980
Hey, Sarah.

56:21.023 --> 56:22.195
Hey, Jacob.

56:22.481 --> 56:24.936
I take my shoes off for you there, see?

56:24.937 --> 56:25.818
Thank you.

56:26.152 --> 56:27.694
Oh, uh...

56:28.200 --> 56:29.363
It's a nice shirt.

56:29.950 --> 56:31.563
Ta-da! Ha ha.

56:32.451 --> 56:34.443
Here, let me do that.

56:34.744 --> 56:36.239
Hey, I gotta pee.

56:36.413 --> 56:37.528
Yeah, go ahead.

56:41.142 --> 56:43.003
- Hi, baby.
- Hey.

56:43.255 --> 56:46.173
- You brought him here?
- Yeah. I invited him for dinner.

56:47.509 --> 56:49.954
Oh! Good.
Good, good.

56:50.389 --> 56:53.849
OK...
So he's gonna do it?

56:56.018 --> 56:57.774
I had to promise him the farm.

56:57.775 --> 56:59.950
You what?
Wait, I thought you said...

57:00.000 --> 57:02.359
we agreed that you were
gonna say something.

57:02.455 --> 57:05.283
Where's he supposed to go,
Sarah, huh? I mean...

57:05.284 --> 57:08.000
What's he gonna do, drive away?

57:08.121 --> 57:11.195
I don't know, honey. I don't know,
but if he stays, we get caught.

57:12.522 --> 57:14.399
I know, I know. It's just...

57:14.581 --> 57:16.206
It's just a matter of
time before he screws up.

57:16.374 --> 57:18.866
I know. That's not what I'm saying.
I just...

57:23.675 --> 57:25.714
I just wish he could, that's all.

57:31.100 --> 57:33.591
No, no, you remember what she did?

57:33.769 --> 57:37.898
She was so freaked out that she called
the volunteer fire department,

57:38.066 --> 57:39.477
and then, remember,
they came out...

57:39.651 --> 57:41.858
- Oh, yeah, there was all of dad's buddies...
- All his drinkin' buddies.

57:42.495 --> 57:43.712
Yeah, yeah.

57:43.822 --> 57:45.400
That's... that's all the volunteer
fire department was,

57:45.022 --> 57:47.654
was guys he knew, you know?
So they show up...

57:47.702 --> 57:50.703
And he's sitting there in the kitchen
with that ice pack on his face.

57:50.872 --> 57:55.701
That's ridiculous. He felt like an idiot,
'cause they're all gathered in there

57:53.336 --> 57:56.914
like there's some huge
murder going down, you know?

57:57.000 --> 57:58.863
Shh, shh.

58:05.639 --> 58:07.081
OK.

58:09.018 --> 58:10.927
Well, back on call.

58:11.646 --> 58:13.572
Hey, how about some more wine?
You got a full glass here.

58:13.648 --> 58:16.684
What's it like, a walkie-talkie, Sarah,
kind of like a baby walkie-talkie?

58:16.860 --> 58:18.652
Yeah, yeah.
It's kinda cool.

58:18.821 --> 58:21.739
Remember, we had that thing we did
with them little walkie-talkies?

58:21.908 --> 58:24.113
- Oh, yeah.
- You got that kit for Christmas.

58:24.410 --> 58:25.573
Remember that?

58:26.748 --> 58:27.790
Yeah.

58:27.791 --> 58:29.042
Yeah.

58:29.332 --> 58:32.998
You know, it's weird.
I think... I think about that stuff.

58:31.805 --> 58:32.998
I think it's kinda weird...

58:33.170 --> 58:34.961
You remember everything, too,
don't you?

58:35.255 --> 58:38.506
Well, yeah. I was always...
I was always talking to dad.

58:39.719 --> 58:40.999
I know you were.

58:41.262 --> 58:44.139
I was always figuring out
what's going on, you know?

58:44.175 --> 58:46.339
I was always nervous about
shit, you know, I guess.

58:46.477 --> 58:48.386
But I tell you what, he's a...

58:50.064 --> 58:54.394
If he... if he had the still
like we got goin' on right now, you know?

58:55.319 --> 58:57.028
He would... he would... he
would have done the same thing.

58:57.197 --> 58:59.771
I don't know, I don't know.
I guess so.

58:59.950 --> 59:01.811
I mean, 'cause that's what he...

59:01.854 --> 59:04.278
He always wanted to get
everything set up, you know.

59:04.580 --> 59:08.164
I mean, he always wanted to have enough
to just take care of things and relax, you know.

59:08.257 --> 59:09.257
Yeah.

59:09.396 --> 59:13.338
He never quite had that,
so I think he'd done it.

59:12.255 --> 59:14.955
But, uh, I tell you what, he'd still...

59:15.716 --> 59:18.059
I guarantee you, if he'd had this,
he'd still be here.

59:18.100 --> 59:19.639
He'd never have done that.

59:24.645 --> 59:25.889
Done what?

59:26.313 --> 59:30.146
Killed hisself, you know.
It just wouldn't have happened.

59:30.850 --> 59:32.279
What?

59:33.405 --> 59:35.065
What are you talking about?

59:35.657 --> 59:37.615
Hank, dad killed himself,
you know that?

59:39.494 --> 59:41.534
What?
What are you talking about?

59:42.039 --> 59:44.578
Come on, what are you talking about?
They were drunk, they had a wreck.

59:44.751 --> 59:46.765
That's out on Jack's spur road.

59:46.800 --> 59:48.750
That's like that ramp is...
Where he went every day?

59:48.838 --> 59:52.504
You ain't gonna roll away
on a ramp like that.

59:53.010 --> 59:55.679
He'd be on that thing
8,000 times a year, you know.

59:56.138 --> 59:58.808
You think all of a sudden
he forgot his way?

59:59.308 --> 1:00:00.685
Good grief!

1:00:04.148 --> 1:00:07.000
He figured that, you know,
all that insurance money, it'd be...

1:00:07.037 --> 1:00:10.990
You know, it'd take care of the whole
deal that he wanted to... you know...

1:00:11.130 --> 1:00:14.823
- What? No, no. What? Wait...
- You know that, Hank.

1:00:15.786 --> 1:00:17.529
I mean, think about it.

1:00:56.000 --> 1:01:00.050
I guess what I'm trying to say is,
well, maybe I misjudged you, Hank.

1:01:00.150 --> 1:01:07.000
'Cause, I mean, you're a bit more,
well, I don't know, let's... let's say...

1:01:07.380 --> 1:01:12.111
serious... ha ha ha... than a guy like me.
And, you know, maybe sometimes...

1:01:12.150 --> 1:01:16.000
you can come across like you
sort of got a stick up your ass.

1:01:16.100 --> 1:01:20.608
I... I... I mean to... someone who
doesn't really know you, to...

1:01:20.758 --> 1:01:24.511
to someone who can't get beneath
that first impression.

1:01:24.613 --> 1:01:29.105
And, OK, OK, maybe...
Maybe sometimes...

1:01:29.243 --> 1:01:34.605
Well... I can come off
a little bit like an asshole.

1:01:34.606 --> 1:01:35.962
You think?
No, come on.

1:01:35.806 --> 1:01:37.162
Yeah. Oh, no, no, no! No.

1:01:39.011 --> 1:01:40.802
I know what I'm talking about.

1:01:43.891 --> 1:01:45.054
But fuck it.

1:01:46.144 --> 1:01:48.101
It's all in the past, right?

1:01:49.539 --> 1:01:50.685
What do you say?

1:01:51.234 --> 1:01:53.464
- Come on.
- Sounds good to me.

1:01:53.527 --> 1:01:57.135
- Hell, yes. Live and let live.
- Live and let live.

1:01:59.409 --> 1:02:01.152
I gotta take a leak.

1:02:07.251 --> 1:02:08.330
Don't look at me like that.

1:02:09.871 --> 1:02:10.712
Whoo!

1:02:10.713 --> 1:02:11.827
Jerk!

1:02:19.849 --> 1:02:21.722
What, you think that's funny?

1:02:22.422 --> 1:02:24.523
- Ahh!
- Ahh, what, huh?

1:02:24.559 --> 1:02:26.803
I'm asking you, you think it's funny tripping
a guy on the way to the fucking can?

1:02:26.982 --> 1:02:29.651
- Look, buddy...
- Oh, don't buddy me! What the...

1:02:29.860 --> 1:02:33.254
See, that right here is my buddy.
This guy right here is my buddy.

1:02:33.350 --> 1:02:36.157
You're not my fucking
buddy, huh, you got it?

1:02:36.300 --> 1:02:37.410
Come on up here!
Come on up here!

