1:17:43.589 --> 1:17:45.049
They were fighting.

1:17:48.387 --> 1:17:50.593
Lou got really mad.

1:17:51.098 --> 1:17:54.052
He shot the walls, he shot the ceiling.

1:17:55.687 --> 1:17:57.430
Then what did we do?

1:17:59.065 --> 1:18:00.974
We ran out to the truck.

1:18:01.235 --> 1:18:04.458
You ran outside with Jacob,
'cause, uh...

1:18:04.556 --> 1:18:11.284
Jacob said, uh... he ran out to get
his rifle on his own. He said, uh...

1:18:11.300 --> 1:18:13.500
See, he said, uh...

1:18:13.600 --> 1:18:17.411
"Lou ran you out of the house
after he shot Nancy."

1:18:18.588 --> 1:18:19.936
Jacob said that?

1:18:23.381 --> 1:18:24.424
Huh...

1:18:31.226 --> 1:18:33.054
Well, I suppose...

1:18:34.814 --> 1:18:36.854
I can see how it might've seemed
that way to him.

1:18:42.072 --> 1:18:43.483
Because...

1:18:45.660 --> 1:18:47.652
he did... he did go out
to the truck alone.

1:18:50.040 --> 1:18:52.115
I followed him, but...

1:18:53.335 --> 1:18:55.208
then, when I heard the shot...

1:18:56.797 --> 1:18:58.588
and Nancy got killed...

1:18:59.384 --> 1:19:01.709
I turned back toward the house...

1:19:02.178 --> 1:19:06.888
I was on the porch
wh-when Lou started outside...

1:19:07.684 --> 1:19:11.220
And that's when I turned
to run out into the yard.

1:19:13.358 --> 1:19:14.389
So...

1:19:17.070 --> 1:19:18.445
I guess...

1:19:19.907 --> 1:19:23.952
I... I can see how it might've seemed that
way to Jacob, that I was running outside.

1:19:28.433 --> 1:19:29.475
Yeah.

1:19:34.173 --> 1:19:38.918
Go home, Hank. We'll, uh...
I think we got what we need for right now.

1:19:40.054 --> 1:19:42.343
- "May they rest in peace."
- May they rest in peace.

1:19:43.016 --> 1:19:45.500
"And may their souls and the souls"

1:19:45.519 --> 1:19:49.000
"of all the faithful departed, through
the mercy of God, rest in peace."

1:19:50.253 --> 1:19:51.604
- Amen.
- Amen.

1:19:51.751 --> 1:19:53.875
In the name of the father,
the son, and the holy spirit...

1:20:05.994 --> 1:20:07.193
Hey.

1:21:16.205 --> 1:21:17.782
Oh, I think the little
baby's ready to come out.

1:21:17.956 --> 1:21:19.581
Maybe she's getting a little cold.

1:21:20.701 --> 1:21:23.778
Whoa...
Yeah...

1:21:24.795 --> 1:21:25.733
Shh...

1:21:30.890 --> 1:21:32.800
Shh...

1:21:32.890 --> 1:21:35.096
- Who could that be?
- I don't know.

1:21:38.980 --> 1:21:40.309
It's Carl.

1:21:51.538 --> 1:21:53.537
Hey, Carl.

1:21:53.538 --> 1:21:56.373
I hope I didn't wake you, Hank.
I saw a light was still on.

1:21:56.541 --> 1:22:00.076
Oh, no, no. Just, you know,
getting ready for bed.

1:22:03.633 --> 1:22:06.302
I hate like hell to have
to do this to you, Hank.

1:22:10.225 --> 1:22:13.597
I was, uh... driving out by
Lou Chambers' place, and, uh...

1:22:14.312 --> 1:22:17.895
I saw your brother's truck parked
out in the middle of the road.

1:22:18.400 --> 1:22:20.059
I could barely squeeze around it.

1:22:20.903 --> 1:22:22.811
I found him inside the house
passed out in an armchair.

1:22:25.032 --> 1:22:27.606
Oh. I appreciate
you bringing him here.

1:22:28.369 --> 1:22:30.611
I... I mean, I hope
it wasn't too much...

1:22:31.957 --> 1:22:36.251
I know you guys had a real rough time.
Just... have a talk with him, ok?

1:22:36.420 --> 1:22:38.828
And I'll try to keep an eye on him, too.

1:22:40.507 --> 1:22:43.509
Come on, what the hell
were you thinking about, huh?

1:22:43.803 --> 1:22:46.377
That's the last place in the world
you oughta be.

1:22:48.267 --> 1:22:52.479
God, I just about had a heart attack
when Carl knocked on the door.

1:22:54.941 --> 1:22:56.732
We gotta be careful.

1:22:58.236 --> 1:23:00.028
Can't take any chances.

1:23:05.995 --> 1:23:07.200
Get yourself over.

1:23:07.219 --> 1:23:08.470
There we go.

1:23:12.336 --> 1:23:13.498
Comfortable?

1:23:15.381 --> 1:23:18.964
Only I don't think I should be here
in the baby's room. It's... it's clean in here.

1:23:19.677 --> 1:23:22.465
What? It's OK.
The baby sleeps with us.

1:23:24.307 --> 1:23:25.802
Hey, you remember this?

1:23:26.435 --> 1:23:28.676
Everything goes to sleep.

1:23:30.022 --> 1:23:33.720
Your head goes to sleep.
Remember when dad used to do that?

1:23:33.752 --> 1:23:35.420
Your head goes to sleep.

1:23:35.421 --> 1:23:37.475
Your shoulders go to sleep.

1:23:37.505 --> 1:23:38.965
Your arms go to sleep.

1:23:39.324 --> 1:23:41.281
Your back goes to sleep.

1:23:41.743 --> 1:23:43.783
Hank, do you ever feel evil?

1:23:52.505 --> 1:23:53.668
I do.

1:23:55.383 --> 1:23:56.962
I feel evil.

1:24:23.123 --> 1:24:25.994
You know, maybe I can get
a family of my own now.

1:24:26.877 --> 1:24:28.752
I mean, with the money and all.

1:24:35.554 --> 1:24:38.306
Why? Don't you think somebody
would marry me if I'm rich?

1:24:39.058 --> 1:24:40.172
You don't need money for that.

1:24:42.000 --> 1:24:43.000
Hank.

1:24:43.229 --> 1:24:47.393
Hey, come on.
What about... What was her name?

1:24:47.568 --> 1:24:48.784
Carrie Richards?

1:24:49.862 --> 1:24:52.400
She liked you even though
you were broke-dick.

1:24:55.994 --> 1:24:59.079
Oh, her. Yeah.
That was a whole different deal.

1:24:59.184 --> 1:25:00.225
That was...

1:25:00.373 --> 1:25:03.992
Her... her friends, they pitched in
100 bucks altogether

1:25:04.211 --> 1:25:07.415
and betted her that she wouldn't
go steady with me for a month.

1:25:13.722 --> 1:25:15.265
Jesus, Jacob.

1:25:19.145 --> 1:25:21.018
I thought you guys had a thing.

1:25:26.914 --> 1:25:28.165
I don't know. It...

1:25:28.489 --> 1:25:30.197
It weren't that bad.

1:25:32.911 --> 1:25:35.449
I mean, actually,
it was kind of cool.

1:25:35.789 --> 1:25:40.451
We used to walk around
together a lot, you know.

1:25:38.624 --> 1:25:39.875
Take walks, you know?

1:25:43.089 --> 1:25:45.627
And, uh, we talked about
all kinda cool stuff.

1:25:47.010 --> 1:25:51.090
I held hands with her one time.
We were walking around,

1:25:51.264 --> 1:25:54.799
but my hand sweated so much
she kinda had to let it go.

1:25:56.187 --> 1:25:57.978
I was nervous, I guess.

1:25:59.190 --> 1:26:03.058
But it was cool.
When the month was over, she, uh...

1:26:03.653 --> 1:26:08.529
You know, kinda would say hi to me
sometimes in the hallway when I'd see her.

1:26:10.495 --> 1:26:11.739
She didn't have to do that.

1:26:12.371 --> 1:26:13.866
That was cool of her.

1:26:18.044 --> 1:26:22.292
God, Hank, you know, I've never...
I've never even kissed a girl before.

1:26:27.848 --> 1:26:33.000
And you know what? If being rich will
change that, I'm all for it. I don't care.

1:26:33.688 --> 1:26:37.389
I just wanna feel it, you know? I just wanna
know what people do, you know?

1:26:37.567 --> 1:26:40.687
I don't care if it's 'cause of the money.

1:26:54.680 --> 1:26:57.294
Hank?
I'm gonna be happy now, right?

1:26:58.882 --> 1:27:00.210
Sure you are.

1:27:00.802 --> 1:27:02.130
We all are.

1:27:04.848 --> 1:27:06.591
Yeah, that's right.
We all are.

1:27:07.934 --> 1:27:11.600
You know what? I'm gonna, you know,
buy back the farm, you know?

1:27:12.022 --> 1:27:15.723
And have, uh... And have a lot of kids,
'cause I'll meet this nice girl

1:27:15.901 --> 1:27:18.689
and she'll be really cool to me
and be really nice.

1:27:18.863 --> 1:27:21.734
Just normal,
a normal woman, you know.

1:27:23.785 --> 1:27:27.783
And, uh... And then you and Sarah
will come over and bring Amanda,

1:27:28.291 --> 1:27:30.828
and we'll all sit around
and tell stories and stuff.

1:27:31.001 --> 1:27:34.870
We'll drink on the porch
like dad and Uncle Ted used to do.

1:27:35.018 --> 1:27:36.860
- You know?
- Yeah.

1:28:03.539 --> 1:28:05.532
He nod off on you, Jack?

1:28:06.763 --> 1:28:07.910
Hey, Carl.

1:28:26.648 --> 1:28:29.436
Gettin' a bit thin
up top there, Hank.

1:28:32.446 --> 1:28:34.522
Don't you have any crimes to solve?

1:28:34.699 --> 1:28:35.778
Maybe.

1:28:37.118 --> 1:28:40.570
Think you could track down Jacob,
bring him by my office tomorrow afternoon?

1:28:40.747 --> 1:28:42.870
Sure. What for?

1:28:43.667 --> 1:28:46.585
Man from the FBI's gonna
be driving through.

1:28:47.088 --> 1:28:49.625
Thought you two might
be able to help him out.

1:28:50.300 --> 1:28:52.506
Seems they're looking for a lost plane.

1:28:52.507 --> 1:28:53.363
Huh.

1:28:57.141 --> 1:28:59.632
- See ya about 3:00.
- You bet.

1:29:09.279 --> 1:29:11.000
Maybe we should just leave.

1:29:11.051 --> 1:29:13.881
Take the money and the baby
and just leave the country.

1:29:13.993 --> 1:29:15.404
Stop it, Hank!

1:29:15.703 --> 1:29:18.373
You'll go in there
and you'll see what he knows.

1:29:18.623 --> 1:29:20.527
If anything looks bad,
we can always move the money.

1:29:20.538 --> 1:29:24.400
- It's still the only thing tying us to anything.
- The connections are just under the surface!

1:29:24.714 --> 1:29:28.000
Sarah, I mean, think about it.
It wouldn't be that hard

1:29:28.176 --> 1:29:30.666
for somebody to just put it all together.

1:29:31.304 --> 1:29:33.877
There's the plane and...
and Stephanson.

1:29:34.057 --> 1:29:35.256
There's Lou and Nancy.

1:29:35.434 --> 1:29:37.473
You've gotta remember how people see you.

1:29:37.645 --> 1:29:39.518
You're just a normal guy,
a nice, sweet, normal guy.

1:29:39.688 --> 1:29:42.262
- They're gonna know!
- No, they won't!

1:29:43.526 --> 1:29:47.026
Nobody would ever believe that you'd
be capable of doing what you've done.

1:29:54.330 --> 1:29:57.781
Well, it was snowin' pretty hard,
so we're not really sure,

1:29:57.959 --> 1:30:01.162
but it sounded kinda like
an engine cuttin' on and off.

1:30:01.714 --> 1:30:05.000
But that was it.
We didn't hear anything more.

1:30:05.635 --> 1:30:08.969
No... No crash.
No engine. Nothing.

1:30:13.268 --> 1:30:14.513
Anything you want to add to that, Jacob?

1:30:18.610 --> 1:30:20.188
No.

1:30:20.610 --> 1:30:22.188
I can't think of anything.

1:30:22.362 --> 1:30:23.737
That's about it.

1:30:24.447 --> 1:30:26.986
It was probably
a snowmobile or something.

1:30:26.987 --> 1:30:27.813
You know?

1:30:41.133 --> 1:30:41.963
Well, guess that's it, guys.

1:30:43.177 --> 1:30:45.300
- Thanks for comin'.
- My pleasure, Carl.

1:30:45.189 --> 1:30:45.919
Good to see you, Carl.

1:30:46.306 --> 1:30:48.547
- Nice to have met you.
- I'll talk to you later.

1:30:52.604 --> 1:30:54.680
Do you think you could
take us out there?

1:30:57.943 --> 1:30:59.318
To the nature preserve?

1:30:59.738 --> 1:31:02.608
Have to go in the morning, I guess,
after the storm passes.

1:31:05.618 --> 1:31:07.030
C-can you tell us what
this is all about?

1:31:08.830 --> 1:31:10.325
Lookin' for a plane.

1:31:11.751 --> 1:31:13.625
There's no way
it's from the armored car robbery.

1:31:13.795 --> 1:31:17.544
This isn't a guess, honey.
The guy from the FBI told me.

1:31:19.467 --> 1:31:21.295
It doesn't make sense.

1:31:22.387 --> 1:31:23.882
The kidnapping made sense.

1:31:24.140 --> 1:31:25.631
He's looking for a plane full of money.

1:31:25.650 --> 1:31:27.600
I mean, how many of those
can there be around here?

1:31:27.770 --> 1:31:29.704
It was hundred-dollar bills, Hank.

1:31:29.750 --> 1:31:31.842
If it was an armored car robbery,
there'd be other denominations.

1:31:31.983 --> 1:31:34.182
There'd be 50s and 20s and 10s.

1:31:34.360 --> 1:31:38.773
Well, congratulations, Sarah.
I guess you know more than the FBI.

1:31:45.062 --> 1:31:46.105
Hank?

1:31:49.043 --> 1:31:50.835
Did he show you his badge?

1:31:51.379 --> 1:31:52.754
Why would he show me his badge?

1:31:53.506 --> 1:31:54.420
Wait.

1:32:05.645 --> 1:32:06.890
It's him, isn't it?

1:32:10.692 --> 1:32:14.524
It's the older one... Vernon.
He's looking for his brother.

1:32:14.697 --> 1:32:16.239
I guy I met today was skinnier.

1:32:16.657 --> 1:32:18.235
He didn't have a beard.

1:32:18.410 --> 1:32:20.900
Well, maybe he lost weight.
Maybe he shaved.

1:32:21.496 --> 1:32:24.283
Well, that doesn't make
a difference, does it?

1:32:24.834 --> 1:32:27.668
I mean, no matter who he is,
I still have to take him to the plane.

1:32:28.671 --> 1:32:30.248
Well, if we think it's him,
you shouldn't go.

1:32:31.090 --> 1:32:31.837
Why not?

1:32:32.217 --> 1:32:36.464
Because he's gonna shoot all 3 of you, Hank.
As soon as he sees the plane.

1:32:37.264 --> 1:32:39.304
That's why he wants you to go,
so he can get rid of the witnesses.

1:32:39.934 --> 1:32:42.342
But if he's really from the FBI,

1:32:42.729 --> 1:32:45.481
and I don't show up,
it's gonna look suspicious as hell.

1:32:50.112 --> 1:32:53.232
I'll call the FBI in the morning.
I'll ask for an agent Baxter.

1:32:53.407 --> 1:32:56.409
That won't work. I'm meeting him at 9:00.
They won't be open before that.

1:32:56.577 --> 1:32:59.034
You can stall them for a bit.

1:33:00.165 --> 1:33:03.949
And, uh, I'll call from here,
and then I'll call you at Carl's office.

1:33:04.461 --> 1:33:06.703
- And what if there's no agent Baxter?
- Then what?

1:33:06.881 --> 1:33:11.792
Well, then you won't go.
You can tell Carl that the baby's sick

1:33:13.305 --> 1:33:15.178
and... and that you have to come home.

1:33:15.390 --> 1:33:16.849
What about Jacob?

1:33:18.101 --> 1:33:20.593
Say he's hung over.
Carl would believe that.

1:33:21.147 --> 1:33:23.685
Whoever the guy is,
you don't want Jacob there.

1:33:25.610 --> 1:33:27.437
It sounds like a B.S. excuse.

1:33:27.612 --> 1:33:29.272
- Hank, what do you want?
- Well...

1:33:30.115 --> 1:33:33.283
Do you want to just walk out there
and get shot by this guy?

1:33:33.453 --> 1:33:35.575
No, I don't wanna walk out
there and get shot!

1:33:35.871 --> 1:33:38.078
- Well, I'm trying to come up with a plan.
- A plan?

1:33:38.875 --> 1:33:43.495
Like the one to take the money back to
the plane, and we end up killing Stephanson?

1:33:43.964 --> 1:33:47.630
Or maybe the one where we tape Lou,
and 2 more people end up dead.

1:33:47.885 --> 1:33:50.377
Is that the sort of plan
you're thinking of?

1:33:50.847 --> 1:33:52.258
Well, I've got a plan!

1:33:53.057 --> 1:33:56.261
I'm taking the money back right now...
All of it.

1:33:56.285 --> 1:33:57.285
- Hank.
- No!

1:33:57.480 --> 1:34:01.941
I'm gonna put it back, and everything's
gonna be just like it used to be.

1:34:02.943 --> 1:34:05.731
That money, goddamn it!
Fuckin' money!

1:34:05.905 --> 1:34:08.527
Is that what you think?
Is that what you think you want?

1:34:08.825 --> 1:34:11.198
Walking off to the feed store
every morning for the next 30 years,

1:34:11.370 --> 1:34:16.198
waiting for tom Butler to retire or die
so you can finally get a raise?

1:34:16.709 --> 1:34:18.418
And what about Amanda?

1:34:18.586 --> 1:34:21.790
Do you think she's gonna like growing up
in somebody else's hand-me-down clothes?

1:34:22.132 --> 1:34:24.837
Playing with some kid's old toys
because we can never afford

1:34:25.011 --> 1:34:26.718
to buy her anything new?

1:34:26.887 --> 1:34:28.299
Don't say any more.

1:34:28.640 --> 1:34:29.837
And me...

1:34:32.143 --> 1:34:33.637
What about me?

1:34:38.526 --> 1:34:42.987
Spending the rest of my life, 8 hours a day,
with a fake smile plastered on my face

1:34:43.573 --> 1:34:45.447
checking out books.

1:34:45.826 --> 1:34:48.661
And then coming home
to cook dinner for you...

1:34:48.829 --> 1:34:53.538
The same meals over and over again,
whatever the week's coupons will allow.

1:34:54.460 --> 1:34:58.292
Only going out to restaurants
for special occasions...

1:34:58.465 --> 1:35:01.549
Birthdays or anniversaries. And even
then having to watch what we order...

1:35:01.718 --> 1:35:05.218
Skipping the appetizer,
coming home for dessert.

1:35:05.390 --> 1:35:07.216
You think that's gonna make me happy?

1:35:07.683 --> 1:35:10.720
- That's enough.
- No, no. I haven't done Jacob yet.

1:35:11.187 --> 1:35:13.476
It's back to the welfare office for Jacob.

1:35:13.648 --> 1:35:15.689
The occasional odd job.

1:35:16.026 --> 1:35:17.935
But with Lou gone now...

1:35:19.030 --> 1:35:22.649
Just himself and his dog all alone in that filthy
apartment. How long do you give him, Hank?

1:35:22.826 --> 1:35:24.106
Stop it!

1:35:27.914 --> 1:35:29.326
Sounds wonderful, doesn't it?

1:35:30.251 --> 1:35:31.958
Everything just like it used to be.

1:35:42.389 --> 1:35:43.504
<i>Federal bureau of investigation.</i>

1:35:44.225 --> 1:35:46.384
I would like to speak to...

1:35:47.061 --> 1:35:49.979
Is there an agent Neil Baxter there?

1:35:51.691 --> 1:35:53.022
Well, if Jacob can't make it,

1:35:53.071 --> 1:35:56.260
that just leaves more of Linda's
homemade breakfast treats to go around.

1:35:56.350 --> 1:35:58.350
Hank, go ahead.
Have one of those.

1:35:58.741 --> 1:36:00.284
Help yourself.

1:36:00.535 --> 1:36:04.615
That's her own special creation there...
Deep-fried dietetic donuts...

1:36:06.583 --> 1:36:10.285
And so inedible, you won't be able
to get enough of it down to be bad for you.

1:36:13.051 --> 1:36:17.756
Hey, this guy, uh... You know, this guy Baxter,
he showed you his badge or anything?

1:36:18.000 --> 1:36:19.344
Badge?

1:36:20.014 --> 1:36:23.348
Yeah. This is kinda stupid,
but, you know, I always wondered

1:36:23.518 --> 1:36:25.013
if they look like
they do in the movies.

1:36:25.187 --> 1:36:26.385
Yeah? How's that?

1:36:27.004 --> 1:36:31.000
Well, you know, kinda
bright and silver with a big "FBI"

1:36:31.029 --> 1:36:32.193
stamped across the center.

1:36:33.029 --> 1:36:34.193
Not really.

1:36:34.407 --> 1:36:35.402
He showed you his?

1:36:35.991 --> 1:36:38.364
Well, no,
but I've seen them before.

1:36:42.290 --> 1:36:43.784
I wonder where he is.

1:36:43.958 --> 1:36:47.244
Well, you know, I bet he'd show it to you
if you just ask him that.

1:36:50.466 --> 1:36:54.001
Hell, he might even let you hold his gun
if you ask him real nice.

1:36:58.809 --> 1:37:00.174
You know what, later on,

1:37:00.200 --> 1:37:04.951
I could take you for a ride in my truck
and make the lights flash for you.

1:37:05.552 --> 1:37:06.352
Yeah?

1:37:06.450 --> 1:37:07.420
<i>- Carl?</i>
- Yes.

1:37:07.520 --> 1:37:10.405
<i>It's Sarah. Hi.
I'm looking for Hank. Is he there?</i>

1:37:10.572 --> 1:37:11.652
Yes, ma'am.
You found him.

1:37:11.824 --> 1:37:15.110
He's standing right here.
He's trying to avoid eating

1:37:15.286 --> 1:37:18.371
one of my wife's homemade donuts.
How's the baby?

1:37:18.915 --> 1:37:22.035
<i>She's not doing so good. That's part
of what I'm calling to tell him about.</i>

1:37:23.378 --> 1:37:24.837
I'm sorry to hear...

1:37:25.297 --> 1:37:28.247
Well, you probably better
tell him that yourself, OK?

1:37:28.408 --> 1:37:29.400
All right. You take care.

1:37:29.427 --> 1:37:30.340
That's your wife.

1:37:31.208 --> 1:37:32.200
Hi, honey.

1:37:32.275 --> 1:37:33.955
<i>- It's him.</i>
- What?

1:37:34.974 --> 1:37:36.679
<i>It's him, Hank.
Come home.</i>

1:37:36.820 --> 1:37:38.280
<i>You gotta get out of there.</i>

1:37:40.416 --> 1:37:42.188
<i>Hank?</i>

1:37:43.317 --> 1:37:44.776
I gotta stay.

1:37:45.194 --> 1:37:46.774
<i>What do you mean you gotta stay?</i>

1:37:46.850 --> 1:37:49.553
<i>We agreed that if I called you,
that you were gonna come home.</i>

1:37:50.117 --> 1:37:51.575
What about Carl?

1:37:53.245 --> 1:37:56.994
<i>I don't know. Tell Carl...
Tell him to give the guy the directions</i>

1:37:57.166 --> 1:37:59.622
<i>and that you two will meet him there later...</i>

1:38:00.128 --> 1:38:01.373
Everybody ready to roll?

1:38:01.671 --> 1:38:03.878
<i>Hank, he's gonna...
He's gonna shoot you both.</i>

1:38:04.049 --> 1:38:05.459
Ready to roll.

1:38:07.189 --> 1:38:08.231
<i>Hank?</i>

1:38:08.389 --> 1:38:09.431
Yeah.

1:38:11.899 --> 1:38:13.776
<i>Hank?</i>

1:38:16.187 --> 1:38:18.643
Well, they're waiting
for me, baby. I gotta go.

1:38:18.755 --> 1:38:20.699
- Carl, how you doin'?
- Good morning. How'd you sleep?

1:38:20.943 --> 1:38:22.500
<i>You come home, OK? Please, baby.</i>

1:38:22.557 --> 1:38:23.516
Sarah.

1:38:24.201 --> 1:38:25.197
OK.

1:38:25.198 --> 1:38:25.979
<i>Wait, Hank!</i>

1:38:26.157 --> 1:38:27.568
Yeah, I'll see you then.

1:38:27.762 --> 1:38:31.300
Ok. Yeah. Yeah,
I'll see you then.

1:38:31.362 --> 1:38:33.271
<i>God damn it! Don't!</i>

1:38:33.415 --> 1:38:34.791
I love you, too.

1:38:35.722 --> 1:38:36.973
<i>Wait! Hank?</i>

1:38:39.630 --> 1:38:40.662
Everything OK?

1:38:41.091 --> 1:38:45.670
Oh, yeah. You know, just, uh...
Some confusion about this evening's plans.

1:38:45.888 --> 1:38:46.717
Where's your brother?

1:38:47.558 --> 1:38:50.426
Oh, uh, Jacob won't be
joining us this morning.

1:38:50.514 --> 1:38:53.182
It seems he tied one on
again last night.

1:38:53.981 --> 1:38:56.650
- Ready when you are, Hank.
- Good. Let's go.

1:39:02.077 --> 1:39:03.641
Oh, no. You
should've asked me.

1:39:04.953 --> 1:39:06.900
Oh, hey.

1:39:06.953 --> 1:39:08.993
I forgot my hat.
I'll catch up with you guys.

1:39:09.164 --> 1:39:11.406
Well, go get it.
It's cold out there.

1:39:12.573 --> 1:39:14.563
You saw that truck right
around the corner, didn't you?

1:39:45.654 --> 1:39:47.218
Shit.

1:41:10.467 --> 1:41:13.137
Oh, this is the place, Hank.
I'm pretty sure of it.

1:41:13.304 --> 1:41:16.800
Look. Right there
is that, uh, nature preserve sign.

1:41:16.850 --> 1:41:18.924
That's where you guys were.

1:41:18.351 --> 1:41:21.500
I guess you're right, but I thought
it was a little further down,

1:41:21.582 --> 1:41:22.900
just, you know...

1:41:22.940 --> 1:41:26.523
And, you know, if it was off over on
that side, that's farmland over there.

1:41:26.694 --> 1:41:28.604
Those farmers probably
would have found it by now.

1:41:28.780 --> 1:41:31.022
The best bet's gotta be over
here in the nature preserve.

1:41:31.200 --> 1:41:35.067
So I think the best idea is each of us take
a different section of the woods...

1:41:35.704 --> 1:41:39.537
Oh, good for Jacob.
This will make things go faster.

1:41:44.088 --> 1:41:45.667
Bring your rifle!

1:41:48.386 --> 1:41:50.627
We'll take a different section of the woods.

1:41:50.804 --> 1:41:53.759
If you or I find it, Baxter, we'll just
fire a couple of shots into the air.

1:41:55.894 --> 1:41:58.931
And, uh, Hank, here, you take that whistle.
And if you find it, just blow it loud as you can.

1:41:59.106 --> 1:42:00.897
We'll all come running.

1:42:12.496 --> 1:42:13.776
I thought you weren't up for this.

1:42:14.456 --> 1:42:15.619
I talked to Sarah.

1:42:18.127 --> 1:42:19.752
Well, I got up, and I felt better.

1:42:20.129 --> 1:42:22.003
You're right. You don't look good.
Something wrong?

1:42:23.508 --> 1:42:25.216
Oh, I just...
I had a rough night.

1:42:25.385 --> 1:42:26.500
Well, let's go, guys.

1:42:27.804 --> 1:42:29.264
- I'll take the center.
- All right.

1:44:15.859 --> 1:44:16.663
Hey! Hey!

1:44:16.774 --> 1:44:18.025
Carl...

1:44:39.203 --> 1:44:40.578
Wait, Carl!

1:44:41.705 --> 1:44:43.433
Get outta there!
Run!

1:44:43.608 --> 1:44:45.036
Hey! Hey! I found it.
It's right down here.

1:44:45.501 --> 1:44:48.075
Pull your gun on him!
Make him show you his badge!

1:44:48.100 --> 1:44:50.499
- What?
- He's got a gun!

1:44:50.500 --> 1:44:51.715
He's got a gun!

1:44:51.716 --> 1:44:54.050
He's not FBI! He's lying!

1:44:54.111 --> 1:44:55.320
What are you talking about?

1:44:55.387 --> 1:44:56.218
Just do it!

1:44:57.807 --> 1:45:00.180
I guess you might as well
just show him your badge.

1:44:59.644 --> 1:45:01.437
All right, all right.

1:45:01.644 --> 1:45:03.437
It's OK, Hank. He's gonna
show you his badge.

1:45:03.689 --> 1:45:05.349
Don't turn your back!

1:45:06.326 --> 1:45:07.369
Aah!

1:45:12.156 --> 1:45:13.532
Where's my money?

1:45:14.666 --> 1:45:15.813
Where is it?

1:45:22.126 --> 1:45:23.669
It's in the plane.

1:45:24.587 --> 1:45:25.369
Then go get it.

1:45:26.369 --> 1:45:27.469
Come on!

1:45:31.429 --> 1:45:33.765
You waiting for something, genius?
Do it!

1:45:33.814 --> 1:45:34.856
OK, OK.

1:46:04.006 --> 1:46:05.798
Come on! Today!

1:46:19.566 --> 1:46:21.227
OK, I've got it!

1:46:32.956 --> 1:46:35.163
Where the fuck is the rest...

1:46:39.588 --> 1:46:40.751
So you had a piece, huh?

1:46:49.099 --> 1:46:52.136
But you're not the cold-blooded type,
are you, Mr. Mitchell?

1:46:58.026 --> 1:47:00.731
Looks like we're both gonna have
an awful lot of explaining to do.

1:47:03.282 --> 1:47:04.278
Just me.

1:47:19.766 --> 1:47:20.809
Jacob?

1:47:29.636 --> 1:47:31.304
Hank?

1:47:32.982 --> 1:47:34.227
It's ok.

1:47:43.710 --> 1:47:44.543
Don't.

1:47:44.890 --> 1:47:45.516
Maybe...

1:47:45.517 --> 1:47:46.419
Don't. Don't.

1:47:46.420 --> 1:47:47.565
You're gonna mess it up.

1:47:47.207 --> 1:47:49.994
- Mess it... mess it up?
- Just leave him be.

1:47:50.103 --> 1:47:51.145
OK.

1:47:59.470 --> 1:48:01.428
You understand what we gotta say?

1:48:01.429 --> 1:48:02.628
Huh?

1:48:03.600 --> 1:48:08.144
We're gonna tell them that Carl lent me
the gun to signal if I found the plane.

1:48:09.606 --> 1:48:13.307
Then when I saw Baxter shoot him...

1:48:13.611 --> 1:48:15.236
We can't do this, Hank.

1:48:15.405 --> 1:48:16.400
What do you mean we can't?

1:48:16.781 --> 1:48:18.608
We're gonna have to tell on ourselves.

1:48:20.493 --> 1:48:21.324
No, we don't.

1:48:22.329 --> 1:48:23.609
We... we can't.

1:48:23.610 --> 1:48:24.297
No. No.

1:48:26.083 --> 1:48:28.789
- No. This is gonna work.
- Not anymore.

1:48:33.020 --> 1:48:34.062
Yeah.

1:48:34.385 --> 1:48:36.009
Yeah, it's gonna work.

1:48:38.973 --> 1:48:40.171
It's perfect.

1:48:41.602 --> 1:48:42.749
Come on, Jacob.

1:48:45.439 --> 1:48:48.606
We just gotta get through the next
couple of hours, and then we're home.

1:48:48.776 --> 1:48:50.318
We're home-free.

1:48:56.576 --> 1:48:58.237
You wanna be happy?

1:49:00.997 --> 1:49:02.790
You want a wife and kids?

1:49:03.626 --> 1:49:06.960
Me and you sitting around on
the porch drinking late at night?

1:49:10.717 --> 1:49:13.339
Well, God damn it,
this is what it costs...

1:49:14.513 --> 1:49:16.387
Right here, right now.

1:49:21.009 --> 1:49:21.945
Come on.

1:49:23.009 --> 1:49:23.945
Come on.

1:49:24.065 --> 1:49:27.731
Let's go over this again, make sure
we haven't overlooked anything.

1:49:30.156 --> 1:49:31.982
I wish somebody else
had found that money.

1:49:32.157 --> 1:49:34.151
Well, they didn't. Now quit.

1:49:43.796 --> 1:49:45.920
OK. Baxter came down here.

1:49:46.508 --> 1:49:49.129
He came up behind Carl.

1:49:52.222 --> 1:49:55.508
I was over there.
Yeah, and you were in the woods.

1:49:54.264 --> 1:49:55.411
Yeah. Yeah.

1:49:59.564 --> 1:50:02.684
Yeah. It's gonna work.
It's gonna work. Yeah.

1:50:07.198 --> 1:50:09.653
W-what are you doing?
Now put this back.

1:50:14.289 --> 1:50:17.077
Make it look like
the bad guy did it, Hank.

1:50:20.710 --> 1:50:21.440
What?

1:50:22.256 --> 1:50:23.834
W-we're almost home.

1:50:24.801 --> 1:50:26.259
I'm tired, Hank.

1:50:32.017 --> 1:50:35.967
A-a-and I don't care. It's ok with me.
I'm not... I'm not afraid.

1:50:38.849 --> 1:50:39.858
No, Jacob.

1:50:39.859 --> 1:50:42.267
- I'm not afraid. It's perfect.
- Stop that, Jacob.

1:50:42.289 --> 1:50:43.539
It's... it's perfect.

1:50:42.740 --> 1:50:43.540
No. No.

1:50:43.863 --> 1:50:46.153
Come on, Hank.
Let me do something.

1:50:45.063 --> 1:50:47.353
This is...
This is the only thing.

1:50:47.458 --> 1:50:49.443
See, I don't wanna sit around
the rest of my life

1:50:49.587 --> 1:50:51.359
thinking about this shit.
I can't do it...

1:50:50.621 --> 1:50:52.822
Sit on the porch and drink.
I can't do it.

1:50:52.950 --> 1:50:54.701
So you're gonna have to do it.

1:50:54.877 --> 1:50:55.623
Couple more hours,
we'll be home.

1:50:55.794 --> 1:50:58.998
You can do this, and it's
gonna be perfect for you.

1:50:59.173 --> 1:51:02.507
You got something to go on for, Hank,
and you know it.

1:51:03.636 --> 1:51:05.345
I don't wanna be here.

1:51:07.500 --> 1:51:09.290
No. Please, no.

1:51:09.559 --> 1:51:12.395
Come on, Hank.
Let me do something.

1:51:14.439 --> 1:51:18.652
You just tell the little girl that I...
that, you know, that bear is from me.

1:51:18.915 --> 1:51:20.062
You know?

1:51:34.587 --> 1:51:36.415
If you love me, Hank,
you'll do it.

1:51:38.383 --> 1:51:40.258
I'll give you a chance.
I won't look at you.

1:51:42.347 --> 1:51:44.505
I won't look at you, Hank,
but if you don't do it...

1:51:46.882 --> 1:51:48.133
then I'm gonna do it,

1:51:48.155 --> 1:51:50.889
and then we're gonna both
gonna be fucked, aren't we?

1:51:56.404 --> 1:52:01.100
We don't need to both be fucked.
I'll... I'll do it, Hank, if you don't.

1:52:01.117 --> 1:52:03.075
- No!
- I'm telling you I will.

1:52:11.879 --> 1:52:16.008
Boy, it's... it's funny about f-finding
this fucking plane, wasn't it?

1:52:21.361 --> 1:52:22.403
Jacob!

1:52:43.253 --> 1:52:44.296
Oh, Jacob!

1:53:11.322 --> 1:53:15.450
To someone who's been properly trained,
there are many ways to detect a liar.

1:53:15.702 --> 1:53:19.700
The shifty eyes of detective novels
have a certain basis in fact.

1:53:20.165 --> 1:53:22.288
A wooden or stilted tone.

1:53:23.043 --> 1:53:25.617
Gestures that seem either slightly robotic

1:53:25.796 --> 1:53:28.632
or else unnecessarily expansive.

1:53:30.093 --> 1:53:32.549
Details tend to be vague, slippery.

1:53:34.306 --> 1:53:37.722
Sometimes the suspect will cover his mouth
with his hand when he speaks.

1:53:38.936 --> 1:53:41.938
Did you notice anything like that
in the guy you shot today?

1:53:44.943 --> 1:53:47.399
He was lying to you, Mr. Mitchell.
He wasn't from the FBI.

1:53:47.571 --> 1:53:49.000
His name was Vernon Bokovsky.

1:53:49.001 --> 1:53:52.339
His brother was in that crashed plane
you found out there today.

1:53:52.118 --> 1:53:56.163
Bokovski and his brother were the guys who
kidnapped that McMartin girl last November.

1:53:56.331 --> 1:53:58.704
Remember the one they shot
and dumped in the lake?

1:53:58.917 --> 1:54:01.871
4.4 million in ransom money.
Want to touch it?

1:54:03.339 --> 1:54:04.619
Go ahead.
Go ahead.

1:54:08.804 --> 1:54:09.883
Pretty hefty, huh?

1:54:09.955 --> 1:54:11.928
That's only part of it.
We're still tracking down the rest.

1:54:12.098 --> 1:54:13.474
Yeah. It's just a matter of time.

1:54:14.184 --> 1:54:15.512
A matter of time?

1:54:17.230 --> 1:54:20.270
Well... we had the money for 2 hours
before the kidnappers picked it up.

1:54:20.441 --> 1:54:23.893
Couldn't mark it. We were afraid they'd
detect the markings and kill the girl, so, um...

1:54:24.070 --> 1:54:26.823
We put together a task force of 20 agents,

1:54:26.870 --> 1:54:31.300
and they wrote down as many of
the serial numbers as they could.

1:54:31.370 --> 1:54:34.076
We managed to record just
under 5.000 of them.

1:54:34.249 --> 1:54:35.992
That's 1 out of 10 of the bills.

1:54:37.752 --> 1:54:41.336
Now it's simply a matter of waiting
for the numbers to turn up.

1:54:42.049 --> 1:54:45.659
Can't go around passing $100 bills without
eventually sticking in someone's memory.

1:54:50.855 --> 1:54:52.002
No. No!

1:54:53.461 --> 1:54:54.921
No, Hank. Hank!
Oh, Hank!

1:54:56.774 --> 1:54:58.565
Hank, we can run with it.
We could leave the country.

1:54:58.734 --> 1:55:02.353
We could go to South America
or to Australia or someplace far away.

1:55:02.354 --> 1:55:03.781
Please, Hank!

1:55:03.782 --> 1:55:04.929
Aah! Aah.

1:56:08.439 --> 1:56:12.022
<i>There are days when I manage
not to think of anything at all...</i>

1:56:14.069 --> 1:56:15.398
<i>Not the money...</i>

1:56:16.697 --> 1:56:18.108
<i>Or the murders...</i>

1:56:20.035 --> 1:56:21.232
<i>Or Jacob...</i>

1:56:23.580 --> 1:56:27.661
<i>Days when Sarah and I try to pretend
that we're just like everyone else...</i>

1:56:29.212 --> 1:56:31.418
<i>As if none of it had ever happened.</i>

1:56:33.800 --> 1:56:36.671
<i>But those days are few and far between.</i>
